INSERT INTO `roads_and_bridges_collections` VALUES (1,'zdvkc5a8zpjxv6e8knzutm0h','Contract No. HY/2019/02 Lift and Pedestrian Walkway System between Castle Peak Road and Kung Yip Street, Kwai Chung','Contract No. HY/2019/02 Lift and Pedestrian Walkway System between Castle Peak Road and Kung Yip Street, Kwai Chung','Highways Department','19 December 2019 - 31 December 2023','<p>To construct a pedestrian infrastructure that is convenient, safe, environmentally friendly, and barrier-free, will enhance convenience and accessible pedestrian traffic for local residents, including the elderly and disabled, between the Shek Lei area, Castle Peak Road – Kwai Chung, and Kung Yip Street.</p><br/><p>The project includes construction of a lift and pedestrian walkway system connecting Shek Lei area, Castle Peak Road – Kwai Chung and Kung Yip Street, with 3 lift towers, 2 covered, elevated pedestrian walkways and 2 staircases.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 02:26:22.427000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.686000',NULL,12,36,'en',1.00),(3,'c78bcj6wy133miw5b6thwnr3','合約編號 HY/2019/02 葵涌青山公路至工業街升降機及行人通道系統','合約編號 HY/2019/02 葵涌青山公路至工業街升降機及行人通道系統','路政署','2019 年 12 月 19 日 - 2023 年 12 月 31 日','<p>此項目主要為建造一個方便舒適、安全、環保且無障礙的行人基礎設施，以供當地居民(包括長者及殘疾人士)在石籬、青山公路－葵涌段及工業街之間可以更方便和無障礙通行。</p><br/><p>本項目包括興建一個連接石籬區、青山公路－葵涌段和工業街的升降機及行人道系統，包括興建3座升降機塔、2條有蓋高架行人天橋及2條樓梯。</p>','2025-06-03 02:27:22.888000','2025-07-07 07:27:30.709000',NULL,12,36,'zh-Hant-HK',1.00),(6,'ltijqf4stvdo9svdu3gku4yz','合约编号 HY/2019/02 葵涌青山公路至工业街升降机及行人通道系统','合约编号 HY/2019/02 葵涌青山公路至工业街升降机及行人通道系统','路政署','2019 年 12 月 19 日 - 2023 年 12 月 31 日','<p>此项目主要为建造一个方便舒适、安全、环保且无障碍的行人基础设施，以供当地居民(包括长者及残疾人士)在石篱、青山公路－葵涌段及工业街之间可以更方便和无障碍通行。</p><br/><p>本项目包括兴建一个连接石篱区、青山公路－葵涌段和工业街的升降机及行人道系统，包括兴建3座升降机塔、2条有盖高架行人天桥及2条楼梯。</p>','2025-06-03 02:37:38.436000','2025-07-07 07:27:12.931000',NULL,12,36,'zh-CN',1.00),(8,'gq0lawile6nf2mkavcazrces','Contract No. HY/2016/05 Footbridge connecting Tsuen Wan Plaza, Skyline Plaza and adjacent landscaping area','Contract No. HY/2016/05 Footbridge connecting Tsuen Wan Plaza, Skyline Plaza and adjacent landscaping area','Highways Department','08 May 2017 - 03 December 2019','<p>The major scope of this project consists of construction of a covered footbridge of about 66m in length and about 3.5m in clear width connecting Tsuen Wan Plaza, Skyline Plaza and adjacent landscaping area; construction of a lift and covered staircase at Hoi Shing Road, reconstruction of the existing lay-by at Hoi Shing Road and ancillary works including associated road, drainage, public utilities, lighting, landscaping, electrical and mechanical works, etc.</p>','2025-06-03 02:38:48.608000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.922000',NULL,12,36,'en',2.00),(10,'blijm6c8d7499tqwcqf6e59l','Contract No. HY/2016/04 Elevated Walkway between Tong Ming Street and Tong Tak Street , Tseung Kwan O','Contract No. HY/2016/04 Elevated Walkway between Tong Ming Street and Tong Tak Street , Tseung Kwan O','Highways Department','30 December 2016 - 03 March 2021','<p>The main purpose of this project is to construct an elevated walkway connecting the existing footbridge across Tong Ming Street to the shopping mall above Tseung Kwan O MTR Station and a lift at the end of the elevated walkway near Tong Tak Street to provide a comfortable and convenient access for residents (especially the elderly) of Tseung Kwan O town centre. The existing cycle parking area at Tong Ming Street is to be reconstructed and expanded to increase the number of cycle parking spaces for use by the residents of the area.</p><br/><p>This contract mainly comprises construction of an elevated walkway of about 180 m in length and about 5 m in clear width, connecting the existing footbridge across Tong Ming Street to the shopping mall above Tseung Kwan O MTR Station; construction of a lift at the end of the proposed elevated walkway near Tong Tak Street; reconstruction and expansion of the existing cycle parking area; and ancillary works, including associated road, drainage, public utilities, public lighting, landscaping, and electrical and mechanical works.</p>','2025-06-03 02:39:46.697000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.745000',NULL,12,36,'en',3.00),(12,'pbw0ekgzloczt47laihptckd','Contract No. KL/2015/03 Kai Tak Development – Stage 3B Infrastructure at Former North Apron Area','Contract No. KL/2015/03 Kai Tak Development – Stage 3B Infrastructure at Former North Apron Area','Civil Engineering and Development Department','22 December 2016 - 31 January 2022','<p>This project involves the construction of a section of dual two-lane Road L2, an elevated walkway LW4 across Prince Edward Road East and a 180m long pedestrian subway SW4 which connects the Kai Tak Development Area and Choi Hung Estate using trenchless method.</p><br/><p>The project utilizes Hong Kong&#x27;s first Rectangular Tunnel Boring Machine (RTBM), which enhances work safety and enables more effective management and control of tunnel construction risks. Additionally, the use of prefabricated tunnel segments produced at an off-site precast yard improves the quality of work and provides a safer work environment for the workers.</p>','2025-06-03 02:40:29.146000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.757000',NULL,12,36,'en',4.00),(14,'l769y69ukmxgfonaptttwp44','Contract No. NE/2015/02 Tseung Kwan O - Lam Tin Tunnel, Road P2 and Associated Works','Contract No. NE/2015/02 Tseung Kwan O - Lam Tin Tunnel, Road P2 and Associated Works','Civil Engineering and Development Department','29 July 2016 - 28 September 2023','<p>The Tseung Kwan O - Lam Tin Tunnel (TKO-LTT) is intended to address growing external traffic demands from Tseung Kwan O&#x27;s ongoing development. Together with the proposed Trunk Road T2 and Central Kowloon Route, the TKO-LTT will form the express Route 6 network linking West Kowloon and Tseung Kwan O.</p><br/><p>This project is part of the TKO-LTT which includes constructing an 800m dual two-lane highway (Road P2), with around 600m in the form of a depressed carriageway, 200m of which will be covered by a landscape deck. Associated building, civil, structural, marine, electrical, mechanical, landscaping, environmental protection, and mitigation works are also included.</p>','2025-06-03 02:41:00.342000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.729000',NULL,12,36,'en',5.00),(17,'zv9xgpe7q4p79eba7gd93bzz','General Civil Works Contract No. HY/2014/18 Provision of Barrier-Free Access Facilities for Highways Structures - Phase 3 Contract 7','General Civil Works\nContract No. HY/2014/18 Provision of Barrier-Free Access Facilities for Highways Structures - Phase 3 Contract 7','Highways Department','25 November 2015 - 25 November 2019','<p>The Government has been installing barrier-free access facilities at public walkways and launched the “Universal Accessibility” (UA) Programme in August 2012 to proactively provide more barrier-free access facilities to facilitate public convenience in using public walkways.</p><br/><p>The works mainly comprise construction of 18 lifts, 6 ramps and 1 stairlift for 9 existing footbridges, 3 existing elevated walkways and 5 existing subways in 17 locations located in Eastern District, Wan Chai District, Southern District, Kowloon City District, Kwun Tong District, Yau Tsim Mong District and Kwai Tsing District; Associated with works above: civil works, geotechnical works, electrical and mechanical works, modification works for existing structures, roads and drainage works, landscaping works, etc. and Site investigation works as specified in the Contract.</p>','2025-06-03 02:41:52.193000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.591000',NULL,12,36,'en',6.00),(19,'w1cqzqr8f7bite57k6xaz93f','Civil Engineering and Development Department Contract No. CV/2013/08 Liantang / Heung Yuen Wai Boundary Control Point Site Formation and Infrastructure Works – Contract 6','Civil Engineering and Development Department Contract No. CV/2013/08 Liantang / Heung Yuen Wai Boundary Control Point Site Formation and Infrastructure Works – Contract 6','Civil Engineering and Development Department','24 June 2015 - 21 June 2019','<p>The LT/HYW BCP is the seventh land-based BCP between Hong Kong and Shenzhen. At present, there are two land-based BCPs at Man Kam To and Sha Tau Kok. Owing to geographical constraints, however, these two BCPs have little room for further expansion. Situated between Man Kam To and Sha Tau Kok, the LT/HYW BCP will make up for the inadequacies and make cross-boundary transportation and connections between Hong Kong and the eastern part of Guangdong Province as well as the Fujian and Jiangxi Provinces more convenient and efficient. This can help expand Hong Kong&#x27;s economic hinterland.</p><br/><p>It comprises the construction of an approximately 4.6km long dual two-lane Connecting Road connecting the BCP with the proposed Sha Tau Kok Interchange and the associated tunnel ventilation buildings. Provision of sewage collection, treatment and disposal facilities for the BCP and the resite of Chuk Yuen Village and the associated environmental mitigation measures, and Environmental Monitoring and Audit (EM&amp;A)</p>','2025-06-03 02:52:08.606000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.545000',NULL,12,36,'en',7.00),(21,'suibztehsuvis2h547sprmdc','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Design and Build Contract for Footbridge Linking Phase 8 Development','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Design and Build Contract for Footbridge Linking Phase 8 Development','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University','15 June 2015 - 29 August 2019','<p>The major scope of this project comprises the design and construction of a footbridge linking the Main Campus and the Phase 8 development of The Hong Kong Polytechnic University. The footbridge is designed as a steel bow-string arch structure with a main span length of 68m across the entire Chatham Road South. The pedestrian walkway with an overall width of about 7m and its associated sub-structures are hung from the two main arch beams by high-tensioned steel bar. The aesthetic form of the footbridge is designed according to the concept of &quot;Flying Fish&quot; and echoes with the surrounding iconic buildings of the University.</p><p>The works under the project include the design and construction of pile foundation, pile cap, RC lift shaft structures, lift installation, steel footbridge structure and its associated sub- structures, architectural works and finishes, building services works, footbridge connection works involving alternation and addition works to the existing Block Z at Phase 8 development.</p>','2025-06-03 02:52:56.166000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.543000',NULL,12,36,'en',8.00),(23,'j0nyjfqecqwnzwsq35ch5gbv','Contract No. CV/2014/03 Provision of Universal Access Facilities for Highway Structures – Package 1 Contract 1','Contract No. CV/2014/03 Provision of Universal Access Facilities for Highway Structures – Package 1 Contract 1','Civil Engineering and Development Department','13 April 2015 - 12 April 2019','<p>The Government has been implementing measures to improve accessibility and usability of public facilities for all members of the community. In August 2012, the &quot;Universal Accessibility&quot; (UA) Programme was launched to proactively provide more barrier-free access facilities, such as ramps, lifts and tactile guide paths, in order to enhance the convenience and inclusivity of public walkways for users.</p><br/><p>This project consists of provision of 16 nos. of lifts in 8 locations, with 4 locations on the Hong Kong Island and 4 locations on the Kowloon Peninsula.</p>','2025-06-03 02:53:46.537000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.682000',NULL,12,36,'en',9.00),(25,'co7iiotfr7kkf2r210kc4tze','Contract No. HY/2013/12 Tuen Mun – Chek Lap Kok Link Northern Connection Toll Plaza and Associated Works','Contract No. HY/2013/12 Tuen Mun – Chek Lap Kok Link Northern Connection Toll Plaza and Associated Works','Highways Department','21 July 2014 - 21 September 2019','<p>The Tuen Mun–Chek Lap Kok Link (TM-CLKL) enhances connectivity between the New Territories, Lantau, the Hong Kong-Zhuhai-Macau Bridge (HZMB), and the airport. The new road reduces travel distance between the northwest and the airport by up to 22 km. The Northern connecting road section of TM-CLKL connecting road connects Tuen Mun Area 40 with the HZMB Hong Kong Port (HKP) via a sub-sea tunnel. The Southern connecting road section links the Hong Kong Port to North Lantau on via a series of viaducts.</p><br/><p>This project mainly comprises construction of the Northern connecting road section’s toll plaza covering an area of approximately 5.4 hectares and associated structures, carriageways and footbridge, as well as modification and realignment of sections of Lung Mun Road and Lung Fu Road at Tuen Mun, and associated works.</p>','2025-06-03 02:54:28.009000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.731000',NULL,12,36,'en',10.00),(27,'ayodlar9yg42icmd51xqbfjq',' Kai Tak Development - Stage 3A Infrastructure at Former North Apron Area (Contract No. KL/2012/02)','\nKai Tak Development - Stage 3A Infrastructure at Former North Apron Area ','Civil Engineering and Development Department','15 July 2013 - 27 April 2017','<p>The major works of this contract included construction of new roads about 890 metres (m) in total length covering L1, Road L11 and a slip road linking Prince Edward Road East (PERE) to Road D1, a vehicular underpass about 225m long across part of Prince Edward Road East , a new pedestrian subway of about 205m long, and extension of an existing subway about 60m in total length, across PERE, modification and widening of existing roads in former Kai Tak Airport north apron area and San Po Kong area, construction of associated footpaths, street lighting, traffic aids, drainage, sewerage, water mains, landscaping works and electrical and mechanical works, and provision of necessary environmental mitigation measures and implementation of an environmental monitoring and audit programme associated with the above works.</p>','2025-06-03 02:55:38.044000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.166000',NULL,12,36,'en',11.00),(29,'uaikljo85g4lkxlztz3z53r2','Shatin to Central Link Contract No. 1108 Kai Tak Station and Associated Tunnels','Shatin to Central Link Contract No. 1108 Kai Tak Station and Associated Tunnels','MTR Corporation Limited','25 April 2013 - 18 November 2018','<p>The Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a government funded concessionary project providing a strategic rail corridor from Shatin to Central. One of the contracts of the Shatin to Central Link (SCL), the works comprise the construction of the Kai Tak Station and associate tunnels.</p><p>Consisting of 2 levels of RC box structure constructed by cut and cover method, this underground station is located in centre of Kai Tak Development Area. Upon completion of the project, Kai Tak residents will benefit as crossing the harbour will take much less time.</p>','2025-06-03 02:56:19.772000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.334000',NULL,12,36,'en',12.00),(31,'o479udtrplskn4jaohsr2lsk','Contract No. HK/2012/08 – Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central – Wan Chai Bypass at Wan Chai West','Contract No. HK/2012/08 – Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central – Wan Chai Bypass at Wan Chai West','Civil Engineering and Development Department','31 January 2013 - 28 November 2018','<p>The key purpose of Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.</p><p>This is one of the contract in Wan Chai Development Phase II. It is a large scale Reclamation Project with more than 5 Ha. in size. The Project&#x27;s location is from the Central Reclamation Phase III (CRIII) eastern seawall to the west of Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre Extension. The scope of work includes dredging works, seawall works, watermains laying, demolition of existing Expo Drive West Bridge, box culvert extension and stormwater drainage works.</p>','2025-06-03 02:56:53.532000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.070000',NULL,12,36,'en',13.00),(33,'t5n3jwsr4b4t23kwhw3ku5a8','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1111 Hung Hom North Approach Tunnels','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1111 Hung Hom North Approach Tunnels','MTR Corporation Limited','17 December 2012 - 18 November 2018','<p>The Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a government funded concessionary project providing a strategic rail corridor from Shatin to Central. One of the contracts of the Shatin to Central Link (SCL). The scope of work is included Tunnels Works, Foundation Works, Site Formation Works, Bridge Works, Noise Enclosure Works and Demolition Works. This is a challenging project in terms of geographical location and work complexity, as this construction site will pass through the aged urban town Hung Hom where a huge amount of utilities are underground. Due to the location, extensive TTM arrangements and utilities diversion and/or protection has to be undertaken.</p>','2025-06-03 02:57:31.579000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.881000',NULL,12,36,'en',14.00),(35,'he6l4w1kcb40hdavc4rckw78','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No.1106 Diamond Hill Station','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No.1106 Diamond Hill Station','MTR Corporation Limited','17 December 2012 - 18 November 2018','<p>The 17-kilometre SCL was a territory-wide strategic railway project involving 10 stations, amongst which Diamond Hill was one of the six interchange stations. Upon the completion of Diamond Hill Station, it will become a new interchange station for the future SCL and the existing Kwun Tong Line.</p><p>The scope of SCL1106 included construction of a new SCL concourse and platforms and a wide array of enhanced facilities including the installation of 3 new lifts, 12 escalators, additional ticket issuing machines, automatic teller machines, shops, and new public toilet facilities. The scope also includes the relocation of heritage structures and archaeological diggings.</p>','2025-06-03 02:58:11.282000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.037000',NULL,12,36,'en',15.00),(37,'g9onsff8pd56kx202ez8gzsh','Improvement to Pok Oi Interchange','Improvement to Pok Oi Interchange','Highways Department','30 November 2012 - 15 October 2016','<p>The Pok Oi Interchange Improvement Project is a NEC contract of Highways Department in November 2012 to ameliorate the Pok Oi Interchange by relieving traffic pressure on the existing interchange and meeting future traffic needs. The contract includes the construction of an additional flyover at Yuen Long Highway (towards Kowloon) at Pok Oi Interchange; the construction of a connecting slip road connecting the elevated road section and the ground section of Yuen Long Highway to Tuen Mun; building (near Pok Oi Hospital) a section of the left turn lane.</p><p>This project involves construction work in the centre and surrounding area of Pok Oi Interchange which is famous for its busy traffic. Traffic diversion restrictions, a narrow work space and complex public routes are some of the major challenges of this project.</p><p>In addition, this contract is special in that it adopts the NEC3 contract, emphasizing mutual trust and cooperation between contractors, project managers and property owners, promoting early settlement of engineering problems and locking up financial risks as early as possible. Through this contract, the project staff learnt more about the advantages of NEC3, its administrative requirements, working mode and contractual focus. It helped prepare the group for new trends in future government contracts.</p>','2025-06-03 02:58:49.337000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.332000',NULL,12,36,'en',16.00),(39,'rdlyan08qpjqhv81le04132z','Uplifting Works to Promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area (Contract No. CV/2011/02)','Uplifting Works to Promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area (Contract No. CV/2011/02)','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 September 2011 - 31 December 2014','<p>This is a Design and Build project for the uplifting works to promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area. The objective of the works is to enhance the Aberdeen area and aim to further bring out the unique features of &#x27;traditional fishing harbour&#x27; and the local culture of Aberdeen and, by reinforcing the elements of diversified tourism, to enhance Aberdeen&#x27;s attractiveness to both international visitors and local residents.</p>','2025-06-03 03:00:40.779000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.265000',NULL,12,36,'en',17.00),(41,'o6bwb49kal63x53v3xhswzof','Wan Chai Development Phase II - Central Wan Chai Bypass over MTR Tsuen Wan Line (Contract No. HK/2010/06)','Wan Chai Development Phase II - Central Wan Chai Bypass over MTR Tsuen Wan Line','Civil Engineering and Development Department','20 January 2011 - 15 July 2013','<p>The main purpose of the Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.</p><p>One of the contracts of Wan Chai Development Phase II, the works include land formation and construction of the Central-Wan Chai Bypass over MTR Tsuen Wan Line tunnel. As the tunnel must straddle the existing MTR Tsuen Wan Line, major constraint was anticipated during the construction. Since the span-over structure is a heavy massive box, an off-site pre-fabrication method was adopted to avoid imposing loading on the MTR Tsuen Wan Line tunnel. The completed box structure was towed to site by sea for final installation. This construction method proved to be more cost effective and did not cause any impact on the MTR Tsuen Wan Line during the construction.</p>','2025-06-03 03:49:01.346000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.670000',NULL,12,36,'en',18.00),(44,'bsdeljdmebk1ky5hobm5tndj','Provision of Lifts to Two Footbridges across Wong Chuk Hang Road near Yip Kan Street and across Leighton Road and Irving Street; a Bridge across Tuen Mun Road near Tsing To Path and a Subway across Pak Wo Road near Fung Ying Sin Koon','Provision of Lifts to Two Footbridges across Wong Chuk Hang Road near Yip Kan Street and across Leighton Road and Irving Street; a Bridge across Tuen Mun Road near Tsing To Path and a Subway across Pak Wo Road near Fung Ying Sin Koon','Highways Department','01 July 2011 - 30 June 2014','<p>The Government is committed to help the elderly and persons with disabilities to get around town in a hassle-free way.　Barrier-free facilities have been installed at walkways for years. But with an aging population, the process needs to be sped up to make barrier-free access even more user-friendly. The Government have come up with this lift installation programme to provide a &quot;universally accessible&quot; environment.</p><br/><p>This is one of the projects of &quot;Universal Accessibility&quot; Programme which includes the construction of a total of six passenger lifts at two footbridges, one bridge and one subway; demolition and re-construction of three staircases and structural modifications of the footbridges/bridge/subway, associated lighting, drainage, utilities diversion and electrical and mechanical works.</p>','2025-06-03 03:50:08.626000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.024000',NULL,12,36,'en',19.00),(46,'n9edx8nqfbeb5mjunndfmqmc','Contract No. HY/2008/12 Bus-Bus Interchanges on Tuen Mun Road','Contract No. HY/2008/12 Bus-Bus Interchanges on Tuen Mun Road','Highways Department','15 July 2010 - 31 July 2015','<p>The works mainly comprise the construction of a bus-bus interchange on Tuen Mun Road Kowloon-bound near Siu Lam Interchange and Tai Lam Kok roundabout, the widening of Brothers&#x27; Bridge, and the construction of a link bridge with two lifts. It will allow passengers to travel on foot from the holding area at TMR to the holding area at Tai Lam Kok to switch buses. Two lifts will be constructed in connection with the link bridge to provide access to people with disabilities. Its associated civil works include road reconstruction, provision of shelters, drainage, landscaping, traffic aids and street lighting, slope works, waterworks, and provisioning of works for traffic control surveillance.</p><p>The project aims at providing a convenient interchange facility for passengers to switch amongst bus routes from/to Northwest New Territories operating via Tuen Mun Road. This arrangement will not only provide passengers more choices of bus services at the bus-bus interchange, but also greatly enhance the overall efficiency of the bus network in the Northwest New Territories and reduce traffic congestion and road-side air pollution.</p>','2025-06-03 03:51:13.666000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.833000',NULL,12,36,'en',20.00),(48,'pzft8rqymanm36y0lpihca16','Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central-Wan Chai Bypass at Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre (Contract No: HK/2009/01)','Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central-Wan Chai Bypass at Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre ','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 December 2009 - 31 May 2016','<p>The key purpose of Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.</p><p>The group was awarded one of the contracts in Wan Chai Development Phase II, the works mainly include land formation and construction of the Central-Wan Chai Bypass (CWB) tunnel at the water channel between the two phases of Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre (HKCEC) and other associated works.</p>','2025-06-03 03:52:32.265000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.312000',NULL,12,36,'en',21.00),(50,'l4cwxp7wlul1k4fjl7ba6c9o','Tseung Kwan O Further Development – Design and Build of Infrastructure Works for Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill Site (Phase I)','Tseung Kwan O Further Development – Design and Build of Infrastructure Works for Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill Site (Phase I) ','Highways Department','29 December 2009 - 03 April 2012','<p>The Tseung Kwan O Further Development is to improve the overall design of the town with the vision to build Tseung Kwan O into a new town that can boast of its convenience, unique urban design of quality living environment.</p><p>This is one of the Tseung Kwan O Further Development projects, which mainly improves the linkage between Tseung Kwan O Stage 1 landfill site and the adjacent areas for supporting the future recreational developments at the landfill site. It includes the construction of a 2.0km footpath and 1.6km cycle track connecting Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill site and Tseung Kwan O Town Centre South; construction of an approximate 140m long bridge for pedestrians and cyclists; construction of about 1 km of grasscrete paved access and landscape works.</p>','2025-06-03 03:53:20.894000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.426000',NULL,12,36,'en',22.00),(52,'nvhol5snmovdes6wxfo8bsze','Contract No. KL/2008/09 Kai Tak Development – Stage 1 Infrastructure Works at North Apron of Kai Tak Airport for Public Housing and Government Office Development','Contract No. KL/2008/09 Kai Tak Development – Stage 1 Infrastructure Works at North Apron of Kai Tak Airport for Public Housing and Government Office Development','Civil Engineering and Development Department','15 July 2009 - 23 August 2013','<p>The major scope of this project comprises the construction of approximately 2.6m long roads within the Project Site including the control, management, maintenance and diversion of existing roads, 2 footbridge FB1 and FB4, associated drainage including box culverts, sewerage and watermain works, enhancement and extension works of existing subways SW1, enhancement works of existing subways SW3 and SW5, landscape hardworks and softworks and environmental mitigation measures.</p><p>The works include realignment of Concorde Road, and construction of local Roads L2, L3, L4 (part) and L15. In conjunction with these roadworks are the associated street furniture, road markings and tra¬c signs, works for the highways structures (Footbridges, Subway, Enhancement Works) across Prince Edward Road East, construction of drainage, sewerage and fresh and salt water supplies systems to serve the Public Rental Housing (PRH) sites and the KTGO.</p><p>The works also include construction of two box culverts BC1 &amp; BC2, a 2.5m x 2.5m box culvert at Road L3 and its connection to the existing Nullah No. 2 and 3.0m x 2.8m box culvert along the amenity strip of Road L2 and its connection to the existing Kai Tak Nullah respectively, demolition of an existing ramp at the EMSD Headquarters ramp at the EMSD Headquarters crossing the Cargo Circuit, abandon the existing Nullah No. 1 and pipes, construction of 5 footpath connections from Road L2 to Subway SW5 and Wang Kong Road, improvement works at Kai Shing Street / Kai Wah Street junction, construction and installation of electrical and mechanical works for the infrastructure serving the early development at the North Apron area including the PRH sites and KTGO, landscape softworks and landscape hardworks.</p>','2025-06-03 03:54:02.466000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.391000',NULL,12,36,'en',23.00),(54,'wa4topbui3oglezdbprlds22','Retrofitting of Noise Barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridge at Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches','Retrofitting of Noise Barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridge at Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches','Highways Department','08 January 2008 - 09 July 2011','<p>The major elements of Works consisted of:</p>','2025-06-03 03:55:30.237000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.669000',NULL,12,36,'en',24.00),(56,'v8vs541jbcwlu1dejy5nzffg','Business Aviation Centre Expansion Works','Business Aviation Centre Expansion Works ','Airport Authority Hong Kong','16 November 2007 - 25 January 2009','<p>The works include an extension of existing Taxi lane Z3 and additional parking stands with BAC Expansion.</p>','2025-06-03 03:56:37.931000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.412000',NULL,12,36,'en',25.00),(58,'muuu9xb5h09wlfjp8k3hz86k','Road L18A in AREA 18, Tuen Mun (Contract No.TM/2006/02)','Road L18A in AREA 18, Tuen Mun ','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 April 2007 - 29 May 2009','<p>The major works in this project consisted of the construction of an approx. 400m long and 10.3m wide two-lane carriageway with a 3.5m wide footpath on both sides section of about 160m long elevated structure over Wong Chu Road was constructed with a total of about 135m of retaining wall structure at both ends of the elevated structure.</p>','2025-06-03 03:57:24.912000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.394000',NULL,12,36,'en',26.00),(60,'ov5cdjd22c9f937f8eg3ba59','Midfield Parking Stands Upgrading Works','Midfield Parking Stands Upgrading Works ','Airport Authority Hong Kong','23 November 2006 - 05 August 2007','<p>The works consist of the Manufacture, Supply, Construction, Installation, Testing Commissioning and Design of the Midfield Parking Stands Upgrading Works</p><p>Site Clearance</p><p>Airfield Pavement Works</p><p>High Mast Lighting</p><p>System works</p><br/>','2025-06-03 04:05:10.424000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.966000',NULL,12,36,'en',27.00),(62,'pn9l7ahexsma9a6y9dc5umtt','Development of EcoPark in Tuen Mun Area 38','Development of EcoPark in Tuen Mun Area 38','Environmental Protection Department','03 July 2006 - 01 January 2010','<p>The EcoPark is a key element of the strategy that aims to promote the local recycling industry and jump-start a sustainable economy by providing long-term land facility for the environmental and recycling industry. By encouraging and promoting the reuse, recovery and recycling of our waste resources and return them to the consumption loop, the EcoPark will help capitalize the potential of the local recycling industry and alleviate the heavy demand of the Hong Kong landfills.</p><br/><p>EcoPark occupies 20 hectares of land in Tuen Mun Area 38 and will be developed in two phases. Phase I of EcoPark (about 8 ha) will be available for occupation towards the end of 2006 and Phase II (about 12 ha) in 2009. Various environmentally friendly features are being used for the first time in Hong Kong, such as the Sun Pipe, Solar power water faucet, and a Green roof just to name a few.</p>','2025-06-03 04:05:54.799000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.228000',NULL,12,36,'en',28.00),(64,'r4r61n24066xouqwfs2yu5l5','Construction of Sewers, Rising Mains and Sewage Pumping Stations at Kam Tin, Nam Sang Wai and Au Tau in Yuen Long','Construction of Sewers, Rising Mains and Sewage Pumping Stations at Kam Tin, Nam Sang Wai and Au Tau in Yuen Long','Drainage Services Department','29 December 2005 - 30 June 2010','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><br/>','2025-06-03 04:06:56.026000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.113000',NULL,12,36,'en',29.00),(66,'jurgzxg7n08ks5dykib76o49','Airfield Stop Bar Relocation Works','Airfield Stop Bar Relocation Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','19 July 2005 - 09 April 2006','<p>The entire installation works is carried out at night to minimize disturbance to the airfields. Daily detail works plans are carefully planed and perfectly orchestrated at night to maximize productivity under the tight working hours. Although the physical airfield works are only carried out at night, the project requires a 24-hours-a-day input from the project team.</p><br/><p>Pre-cast concrete bases (constructed on site during the day) are perfect for a quick installation of the stop bar light system.</p><br/><p>The transformer housings units of the airfield ground lighting system are imported directly from the United States to meet the stringent requirements for airfields usages.</p>','2025-06-03 11:56:45.111000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.409000',NULL,3,36,'en',30.00),(68,'fbrjrm6guy7bbgtfd7ne6e5x','Sky City Car Park and Utility Works','Sky City Car Park and Utility Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','31 May 2005 - 20 December 2005','<p>Our company is the first to apply the GFA pavement in Hong Kong. GFA is the acronym for granular materials treated with ‘fly ash’ or PFA. GFA is a slow setting, slow hardening mixture which has the benefit of an unbound material in the short-term allowing longer handling time, and as a bound material in the medium to long term provides equivalent if not better structural characteristics of conventional bound materials such as bituminous base course.</p><br/><p>GFA utilizes PFA, a by-product waste from coal-fired energy generation, making it a more economical and environmentally friendly pavement alternative.</p>','2025-06-03 12:00:21.458000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.036000',NULL,3,36,'en',31.00),(70,'mi575lpay63leg04wngop60x','Noise Barriers on Fanling Highway near Choi Yuen Estate and Fanling Centre','Noise Barriers on Fanling Highway near Choi Yuen Estate and Fanling Centre','Highways Department','23 August 2004 - 20 March 2006','<p>The major works of this project is to construct approx. 600m long vertical noise barriers and approx. 2400m long cantilever noise barriers along Fanling Highway.</p>','2025-06-03 12:01:04.651000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.195000',NULL,3,36,'en',32.00),(72,'xaykyxnu4qn7aeizsinty750','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A','Civil and Engineering Development Department','29 June 2004 - 15 October 2008','<p>This is the engineering infrastructure project for Pak Shek Kok Development.  The major works of the project consisted of a significant quantity of site formation works; and the construction of roads &amp; bridges, cycle track, water front promenade, subway, and the associated landscaping works, etc.</p>','2025-06-03 12:01:58.757000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.037000',NULL,3,36,'en',33.00),(74,'a2xe5s15eoba1g0sqg5rhyqw','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road','Highways Department','10 June 2004 - 29 May 2008','<p>One of the most complex and challenging aspects of this project is the temporary traffic arrangements (TTA) while constructing the flyover in the highly congested area of Causeway Bay.</p><br/><p>Numerous traffic simulations analyses are required to study the impact of each TTA scenario. The analyses requires tremendous amount of data to accurately predict the effects of any chosen TTA.</p><br/><p>A 70m long temporary steel off ramp was constructed to maintain the existing traffic flow, with part of the existing flyover initially demolished to allow the construction of the proposed flyover.</p><br/><p>The low soffit level of the proposed flyover with gradients in both directions and the road height clearance requirement coupled with the excessively long span over Victoria Park Road made the design of the falsework decking nearly impossible. The depth of the deck had to meet the various road height clearances, and structural requirements.</p>','2025-06-03 12:02:52.306000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.764000',NULL,3,36,'en',34.00),(76,'ayhg2bgw2i8y8ita0xlwt7pt','Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan','Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan','Territory Development Department','26 March 2004 - 18 November 2006','<p>This project involved different types of civil works in Sha Tin and Ma On Shan with focus on slope, road and drainage works. Due to the inaccessibility of some work areas, special construction methods were employed. For the construction of the 120m long boulder fence at the remote hillside of To Shek Village, a helicopter delivered the boulder fence components to the site and the entire boulder fence was erected by manpower with a specially designed pulley system. While reinstating the 2km long existing seawall along the Ma On Shan promenade, both land and marine equipments were used to transport and place the rock armours. In view of the proximity of the existing seawall to the nearby residents, different environmental protective measures were exercised during the course of construction to avoid nuisance to the nearby public, while keeping the public well informed throughout the construction period.</p>','2025-06-03 12:03:37.077000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.109000',NULL,3,36,'en',35.00),(78,'jqp0ehs8l8xntj9mzsen64a2','Hong Kong International Airport – Cargo Apron Extension Works','Hong Kong International Airport – Cargo Apron Extension Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','24 March 2004 - 31 May 2005','<p>Due to the highly sensitive nature of the area, access is a major obstacle. Construction vehicles have to be inspected and escorted every time they enter into the site for security reasons.</p><br/><p>The supply of fresh concrete into the site next to the airfield runway poses another major constraint. Special site concrete batching plants were constructed. The paving of the Pavement Quality Concrete requires a special automatic paver from Germany, the Wirtgen Slip form paver SP500 to achieve an extremely accurate quality finish of the concrete surface</p>','2025-06-03 12:04:25.269000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.931000',NULL,3,36,'en',36.00),(80,'bmlzogj0ibxsj3qfh59jypob','Improvement Works at Lo Wu Station Platforms 1-3, Link Bridge and Concourse Extension','Improvement Works at Lo Wu Station Platforms 1-3, Link Bridge and Concourse Extension','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','18 November 2002 - 30 July 2004','<p>The project included the installation of 156 nos. of vertical and raking mini piles with 273mm diameter to support the Concourse Extension of the Lo Wu Station and the Link Bridge linking the Concourse Extension to the existing Platform 1. The length of the piles constructed ranging from 20m to 40m with 5m long socket into Grade III rock. The piling works also included the Pre-Drilling prior to the commencement of the piling works to determine the rock head level and the target founding level. It also included the Proof Drilling subsequent to the completion of the pile installations.</p><br/><p>As all the works have to be carried out immediately next to the live railway tracks and inside the busy Lo Wu Station in full operation, the Contractor has to undertake all the necessary safety measures and arrangement to ensure that the train service and the operation of the Lo Wu Station will not be affected by the construction works.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 12:05:13.326000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.099000',NULL,3,36,'en',37.00),(82,'yzydw6xid1v8u0vrtlk45wh3','Public Transport Interchange at Long Ping Station','Public Transport Interchange at Long Ping Station','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','23 September 2002 - 11 October 2003','<p>The Construction of Public Transport Interchanges at Long Ping Station on two sites serves the new West Rail works and includes other works to tie in with works already being constructed under other West Rail Contracts. Our group was awarded this project, which includes the construction of an uncovered Public Transport Interchange at the south of the Long Ping Station for green minibuses and taxis, the works comprise all civil, architectural, landscape and building services works including earthworks, retaining walls, roadworks, footways, drainage works, utility diversions, fencing, finishes and other related works. The PTI at the north of the Long Ping Station is uncovered, catering for franchised bus, residential coaches, taxis and private vehicles. The works consisted of all civil, architectural, landscape and building services works including earthworks, roadworks, drainage works, utility diversions, fencing, finishes and other related works. Other works include the foundation and superstructure works for the staircase, lift-shaft, escalator trough and bridge section to connect to the new section constructed by others, demolition of the existing DSD Staff quarters adjacent to the Yuen Long Pumping Station down to ground level.</p>','2025-06-03 12:05:59.977000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.568000',NULL,3,36,'en',38.00),(84,'ld3s5x93mjwpbom72g8qzugn','Public Transport Interchange at Tuen Mun Station','Public Transport Interchange at Tuen Mun Station','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','23 September 2002 - 31 August 2003','<p>The major element of works consisted of:</p><p>The Works involved considerable interface with other West Rail Contractors, Government Authorities and utilities undertakers, etc.; hence, close liaison amongst these parties as well as the KCRC staffs had been undertaken to ensure smooth execution and timely completion of the Works.</p>','2025-06-03 12:08:12.104000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.843000',NULL,3,36,'en',39.00),(86,'fbr6g3wkerzhm2od6xj419pb','Nam Cheong Station','Nam Cheong Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','01 October 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Nam Cheong Station is the southern terminal of the West Rail. It is an interchange station for the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The structure envelopes the alignments of the existing elevated West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the existing Airport Express Line (AEL) and the MTR Tung Chung Line. It also includes the linking carriageway and the associated elevated flyover system. During the construction stage, the West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line have to maintain normal operations. These requirements greatly increased the difficulties in the construction and required extremely high and stringent construction techniques.</p><br/><p>This station includes the track side platforms at ground level and an underground station hall for both the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The underground station hall was constructed underneath the operating Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line. In order to ensure the operation of the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line, “Top down” construction method was employed. This kind of construction method on such a scale is seldom seen in Hong Kong.The underground station hall and platform design ensured the utilization and development of the underground space, and reduce occupied area at ground level. It also provided a grand outlook of the station. Apart from providing business activities, with the highly efficient pedestrian flow design, the crowds are quickly diverted to the relevant Airport Express Line station, bus station, residential blocks and commercial areas.</p><br/><p>The column, beam structure and foundation design of the station have made provisions for the future development of multi-storey residential blocks on top of the station. The foundations design includes large diameter cast in-situ concrete bored piles, diaphragm walls and driven steel H-piles, etc. Reinforced concrete column structures were reserved at the roof slab of the station for future construction of the multi-storey resident blocks. The multi-storey shear walls of the future superstructures will be supported by the transfer plate at the station roof. This accommodates any future change in the layout of the superstructure.</p>','2025-06-03 12:09:13.933000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.403000',NULL,3,36,'en',40.00),(88,'trtelmv3jf7eopd1kd708j4a','Mei Foo Station','Mei Foo Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved. The quality of living for the local residents was also enhanced.</p>','2025-06-03 12:09:59.156000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.244000',NULL,3,36,'en',41.00),(90,'mer5dsfeh84stflc656z3mcf','Civil and Infrastructure Works','Civil and Infrastructure Works','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 July 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The contract comprises the construction and installation, including the defined design elements, of all Civil and Infrastructure Works, on the West Rail Depot and Kam Tin Station Site. The Works include all site formation, drainage, roads and hard standings, utilities, landscaping, main drainage channel and track bed formation works. The scope of the roadworks includes construction of a two-lane viaduct bridge approximately 660m long across the site fire and public access roads, parking and inter-change facilities.</p>','2025-06-03 12:10:40.023000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.807000',NULL,3,36,'en',42.00),(92,'fig8pc62rlzt4atbvdzoqu9v','Interchange at Pok Fu Lam Road and Sassoon Road','Interchange at Pok Fu Lam Road and Sassoon Road','Highways Department','16 December 1998 - 31 March 2003','<p>Widening of the section of Pok Fu Lam Road fronting Queen Mary Hospital involving the construction of new carriageway (partly on elevated structures) and reconstruction of existing carriageway; re-alignment of the upper section of Sassoon Road at its junction with Pok Fu Lam Road involving the replacement of the existing carriageway with new carriageway (partly on elevated structures); construction of a link bridge linking the re-aligned Sassoon Road and the access road to Queen Mary Hospital; re-alignment of the upper section of Bisney Road at its junction with Pok Fu Lam Road involving the replacement of existing carriageway with new carriageway (partly on elevated structures); demolition of the existing footbridge across Pok Fu Lam Road and construction of a new footbridge at the same location; and associated drainage, landscaping, retaining walls and slope works.</p>','2025-06-03 12:11:29.180000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.059000',NULL,3,36,'en',43.00),(94,'xk2q9bi7qss7qqen4bj9z3w8','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road – Tai Lam Section','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road – Tai Lam Section','Highways Department','01 September 1998 - 31 May 2001','<p>Tuen Mun Road is a highway linking Tuen Mun and Kowloon. This project is to provide a climbing lane and hard shoulder to the existing Eastbound Carriageway of Tuen Mun Road Tai Lam Section and will in addition improve the slopes above Tuen Mun Road.</p><br/><p>The major challenge of the project is the cutting back of the slope, in rock, above the live traffic of Tuen Mun Road at the slope toe. In order to proceed with the excavation safely, the South Rock Knob was excavated, temporarily diverting both the eastbound and westbound traffic away from the north slope. The reinforced fill retaining wall along the existing median was also constructed ahead of any works at the northern slopes so that an additional traffic lane was provided for the temporary diversion of the traffic away from the northern slope. A temporary roadside rock fall fence was then erected at the slope toe with sand cushion behind to catch any blocks of rock that become detached and fall down the slope during excavation.</p><br/><p>Another main feature of the project is the construction of the reinforced fill retaining wall at the Central Median for an extra traffic lane on top. This includes excavation at the existing slope of the Central median while temporarily supporting the existing eastbound carriageway (generally with pipe piles), erect precast concrete panels on the concrete footings and backfilling with selected fill materials sandwiched with galvanized steel reinforcing strips in layers. A temporary steel access bridge was constructed from the works area off Castle Peak Road, spanning across both the West bound carriageway of Tuen Mun Road and Castle Peak Road for the transportation of materials and plants to and from the site.</p><br/><p>Throughout the project, the 3-lane traffic along the eastbound carriageway of Tuen Mun Road has to be maintained at all times. A complicated traffic diversion scheme was adopted to maintain the traffic flow for the full depth carriageway reconstruction.</p>','2025-06-03 12:12:42.093000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.264000',NULL,3,36,'en',44.00),(96,'eqqaybowkaaltd07j8shusj3','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I','Territory Development Department','18 March 1998 - 05 May 2003','<p>Construction of 1.6km long trunk road together with 7.3km of water main of size up to 600mm diameter and associated works. These works included: a 450m long rectangular box culvert and a sea outfall; 4 nos. 6m high retaining wall; installation of 234m pavement soil nail and import of 300,000m³ filling material.</p>','2025-06-03 12:13:35.923000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.261000',NULL,3,36,'en',45.00),(98,'agmd82y87h8obne1i5kridlq','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','11 April 1997 - 26 March 1999','<br/>','2025-06-03 12:14:41.982000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.484000',NULL,3,36,'en',46.00),(100,'n4146sjby637sfmo49fks6ai','Village Flood Protection Works for San Tin Villages','Village Flood Protection Works for San Tin Villages','Drainage Project Division','20 November 1996 - 26 December 2000','<p>The pumping station on raft foundation and its associated storage pond were the major construction works on site. A total of 1,740m long x 3.5m wide, embankment/access road had to be built for flood protection purposes.</p><br/><p>The floodwater flows into the chambers &amp; the pipes system and then to the storage pond. The 5-trough pumping station would begin operating when the floodwater comes up to a certain level upon which the floodwater would pass through a twin-cell box culvert and flow downstream.</p><br/><p>A series of water diversions were required to maintain the stream flow from the San Tin Villages out to the Shen Zhen River.</p><br/><p>For the slope embankment, precast concrete grasscrete blocks are the final surface above the layer of the concrete lining, granular fill &amp; general fill. The grasscrete blocks were designed with open area for hydroseeding and they have to be reinforced together in order to avoid the tidal effect of the floodwater.</p><br/><p>The major difficulties involved in the project were the ground water flow from the adjacent fish ponds and the limited working area along the embankment. Temporary cofferdams formed with sheet piles had to installed in order to cut off the underground water for construction purpose.</p>','2025-06-03 12:15:30.807000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.742000',NULL,3,36,'en',47.00),(102,'zfapn8d1a3zdc6ww3f1w1ru5','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun','River Trade Terminal Co. Ltd','01 November 1996 - 30 November 1999','<p>This project involved large-scale marine engineering works to create a 65-hectare site for the River Trade Terminal in Hong Kong. The experience gained on other major marine projects over the years allowed our company to handle the enormous scope of work required to complete the project within a very tight programme; the first phase of the project was completed a month ahead of schedule. Among our many responsibilities under this contract, which was awarded by a private consortium of some of Hong Kong’s leading companies, was dredging over 3 million cubic metres of marine mud, constructing two 2.1-km long, 1.6-metre in diameter and one 730-metre long 2.1-metre diameter submarine pipelines, building 3.3 km of vertical seawalls, constructing a 530 metre breakwater and extensive ground improvement works. Importation of 11million cubic metres of sandfill was a critical activity of the programme; delivery rates of up to 60,000 cubic metres of sand per day were achieved from our sources in the PRC. Manufacture and installation of over 37,000 seawall blocks was another key activity. To ensure control of the production we manufactured all of the blocks at Wai Kee’s own precasting yard at Niu Tau Island in the PRC. A crucial element of this contract was the careful co-ordination of the follow-on civil engineering and building works.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 12:16:11.194000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.819000',NULL,3,36,'en',48.00),(104,'x1dyajodn599xidn19da5n2q','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works','Civil Engineering Department','01 May 1996 - 30 September 1997','<p>The Works consisted of:</p>','2025-06-03 12:17:00.946000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.504000',NULL,3,36,'en',49.00),(106,'vv8qaq91j048v89numuhsit5','Tuen Mun Area 38 Special Industries Area Development – Reclamation, Seawall, Road & Drains','Tuen Mun Area 38 Special Industries Area Development – Reclamation, Seawall, Road & Drains','Port Works Division / Civil Engineering Department','01 September 1995 - 31 January 2000','<p>This project includes the construction of 450m long vertical seawall, 1000m long sloping rubble seawall, 625m long 4-cells drainage culvert, roads, sewers, drains and watermains and reclamation of 28 hectares of land.</p>','2025-06-03 12:17:38.834000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.983000',NULL,3,36,'en',50.00),(108,'k9629pbm7fkxobaaja3ty3kr','Lantau and Airport Railway Siu Ho Wan Depot, Phase I','Lantau and Airport Railway Siu Ho Wan Depot, Phase I','Mass Transit Railway Corporation','01 January 1995 - 31 May 1998','<p>This was one of the projects of the Airport Core Programme therefore timely completion of the works was critical. The main depot building completion was paramount for the success of the project.</p><br/><p>As there was no land access to the site for this multi-discipline project, careful consideration had to be given to procurement, delivery, and storage of materials.</p><br/><p>The completion of the North Lantau Expressway bridge and associated access roads and embankments within a 3 month period exemplified the project team&#x27;s teamwork &amp; determination to complete the works on time.</p>','2025-06-03 12:18:18.241000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.073000',NULL,3,36,'en',51.00),(110,'fmh85l894b09okl5wuhuxed9','Shanxi Qilin Expressway','Shanxi Qilin Expressway','Shanxi Qilin Expressway Ltd','01 April 2001 - 30 November 2002','<p>Qilin expressway, which runs from the Qi county to the city of Lin Fen, is 177.72 km long and located in the middle south of the Shanxi Province. The width of road surface is 28.50 m and can accommodate 3 lanes of north and south bound traffic each way. Qilin expressway is part of the axial backbone of expressways in the providence. This backbone, measuring 666 km long, stretches from Da Tong to Yun Cheng, crossing the province from north to south. It is also the first expressway project in the province to be financed through the Asia Development Bank.</p><br/><p>The government of the province split the Qilin expressway project into 18 nos of contracts for subletting, and we were contract no. 16. This is a highway construction project of 14.3km in length and 28m in width of asphalt concrete pavement.</p><br/><p>The contract works commenced at the end of June 2001. During the course of construction, we managed the sub-contractors and our own resources to maintain working a minimum of 13 hours per day. The contract works were completed at the end of December 2002 and the project was appreciated by the client.</p>','2025-06-03 12:21:52.387000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.214000',NULL,3,36,'en',52.00),(112,'liq1eaeghs1enjgfuzr4mlvh','Tung Chung Development Phase 1 – Infrastructure','Tung Chung Development Phase 1 – Infrastructure','Territory Development Department','01 July 1994 - 31 January 1997','<p>The bridge was supported by two land abutments and six marine piers. Each abutment was supported by twelve 1.5m diameter land bored piles up to 56m long and each marine pier was supported by twelve 1.5m diameter marine piles.</p><br/><p>The 1.5m diameter permanent linings of the marine bored piles were spliced into 24m to 30m lengths and pitched in position by piling barge.</p>','2025-06-03 12:22:51.933000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.260000',NULL,3,36,'en',53.00),(114,'hkkbfsmvkwnol92k39wa2j0r','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road','Highways Department','01 May 1994 - 30 September 1996','<p>The project includes alignment design and construction at four critical uphill sections (Ting Kau, Tai Lam, So Kwun Wat and Sam Shing Hui) of Tuen Mun Road, with a total length of 8.5km; geotechnical stabilisation on 31 cut slopes and 17 fill slopes; 6 retaining walls; structural reinforcement to six bridges, five underpasses and Sham Tseng Footbridge.</p><p>During the construction, a restricted traffic diversion program was implemented to minimise construction disturbance to the public.</p>','2025-06-03 12:23:52.059000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.008000',NULL,3,36,'en',54.00),(116,'nuwq9b4x07djtiowyb0jo4xf','Sha Tin New Town, Stage II Road T6 and Interchanges','Sha Tin New Town, Stage II Road T6 and Interchanges','Territory Development Department','01 June 1988 - 31 October 1991','<p>Over a thousand tonnes of fabricated steel false work was required for the high level bridge.</p><br/><p>Pile Caps for the marine bridge piers were constructed in precast concrete permanent shells which were lowered into position on the bored piles using strand jacks before making watertight seals and concreting.</p><br/><p>Temporary piles were installed to support the false work for the reinforced concrete V-shaped piers.</p><br/><p>Over 300 large diameter bored piles were constructed by the company.</p>','2025-06-03 12:24:45.148000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.781000',NULL,3,36,'en',55.00),(118,'w25hs3id2t9fwb6g17dm0vic','Sha Tin New Town, Stage II Route5 - Sha Tin Connection, Phase I','Sha Tin New Town, Stage II Route5 - Sha Tin Connection, Phase I','Territory Development Department','01 June 1987 - 31 October 1991','<p>This project involves the construction of the Shatin approach to the Shing Mun Tunnels, and is part of the Route 5 Expressway linking Shatin and Tsuen Wan. The 2km long expressway begins at Tai Po Road near the KCR Shatin Station and rises on a 13 span elevated viaduct over the railway line and Tai Po Road to an abutment halfway along the route to the tunnel portals.</p><br/><p>Along the 1 km expressway near Mei Lam Estate, 1-2m high transparent noise barriers were built to minimize noise disturbance to the local residents.</p><br/><p>There was a high degree of complexity in the construction of cross heads of various sizes. Two main types of false work were specially designed and used in the project.</p><br/><p>A total of 486 precast post-tensioned concrete U-beams were manufactured on site with lifting gantries and transportation equipment designed in house. A wide range of beam lengths added to the complexity. Special gantries were purposefully designed and built by the company for lifting and placing precast beams weighing 65 tonnes.</p>','2025-06-03 12:25:43.571000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.100000',NULL,3,36,'en',56.00),(120,'yhjlv1dk8o3t7zx760ggld0t','合约编号 HY/2016/05连接荃湾广场、湾景广场及毗邻环境美化地带之行人天桥','合约编号 HY/2016/05连接荃湾广场、湾景广场及毗邻环境美化地带之行人天桥','路政署','2017 年 05 月 08 日 - 2019 年 12 月 03 日','<p>本项目主要包括兴建一条长约66米、净阔度约3.5米的有盖行人天桥，以连接荃湾广场、湾景广场及毗邻环境美化地带;在海盛路建造1部升降机及一条有盖楼梯; 重建现有一段在海盛路的停车处以及进行附属工程，包括相关的道路、渠务、公用设施、公共照明、环境美化、机电系统等工程。</p>','2025-06-04 03:21:21.289000','2025-07-07 07:27:12.937000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',2.00),(122,'p8qmy03xjb362jgl1w8ht3oc','合约编号HY/2016/04 将军澳唐明街与唐德街之间的高架行人道','合约编号HY/2016/04 将军澳唐明街与唐德街之间的高架行人道','路政署','2016 年 12 月 30 日 - 2021 年 03 月 03 日','<p>此工程主要目的是兴建一条高 架行人道，连接现时横跨唐明街的行人天桥至港铁将军澳站上盖之商场及在高架行人道近唐德街建造一部升降机以提供一条舒适和便捷的通道，方便将军澳市中心一带的居民（特别是长者）往来。 此外，为增加区内可供居民使用的单车泊位数量，进行唐明街现有单车停泊处的重建及扩建工程。 兴建一条长约180米、净阔度约五米的高架行人道，连接现时横跨唐明街的行人天桥至港铁将军澳站上盖之商场;在拟议高架行人道近唐德街建造一部升降机; 重建及扩建现有单车停泊处;以及进行附属工程，包括相关的道路、渠务、公用设施、公共照明、环境美化、机电系统等工程。</p>','2025-06-04 03:22:26.403000','2025-07-07 07:27:12.932000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',3.00),(124,'suojqup7zfhgy0o6q5udskro','合约编号KL/2015/03启德发展计划－前北面停机坪第3B期基础设施','合约编号KL/2015/03启德发展计划－前北面停机坪第3B期基础设施','土木工程拓展署','2016 年 12 月 22 日 - 2022 年 01 月 31 日','<p>本项目包括建造一段双行双车线道路L2、一座跨越太子道东的高架行人通道LW4，以及一条连接启德发展区与彩虹邨的180米长行人隧道SW4(使用无开挖法技术)。</p><p>项目採用香港首部矩形隧道鑽挖机(RTBM) ，可增强工程安全性，并更有效管控隧道施工风险。此外，使用在场外预製场生产预製隧道主体结构，不但能提升工程质量，也为工人提供更安全的工作环境。</p>','2025-06-04 03:23:22.423000','2025-07-07 07:27:14.556000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',4.00),(126,'azbcxpk0en9bf87e0tyy4tlq','约编号NE/2015/02将军澳－蓝田隧道－主要干路P2及相关工程','合约编号NE/2015/02将军澳－蓝田隧道－主要干路P2及相关工程','合约编号NE/2015/02将军澳－蓝田隧道－主要干路P2及相关工程','2016 年 07 月 29 日 - 2023 年 09 月 28 日','<p>将军澳 - 蓝田隧道(将蓝隧道)旨在应对将军澳持续发展所带来的日益增加的对外交通需求。将蓝隧道连同拟建的T2主干路和中九龙干线，将形成连接西九龙和将军澳的东西行快速公路六号干线。</p><br/><p>本项目属将蓝隧道的一部分，涉及建造一条长 800米的双程双线分隔公路(P2路)。其中约600米为低于地面行车道, 其中约200米以绿化平台复盖。项目还包括相关的填海、土木、结构、海事、电力、机械、环境绿化、环境保护和缓解措施的配套工程。</p>','2025-06-04 03:24:21.229000','2025-07-07 07:27:13.940000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',5.00),(128,'jqen6ndf88kmnmywjypsfskr','合约编号 HY/2014/18无障碍通道设施 - 第三期第七份合约','合约编号 HY/2014/18无障碍通道设施 - 第三期第七份合约','路政署','2015 年 11 月 25 日 - 2019 年 11 月 25 日','<p>政府一直致力为公共行人通道加建无障碍通道设施，于2012年8月推出「人人畅道通行」计划，积极增设更多无障碍通道设施，方便市民上落公共行人通道。</p><br/><p>此工程主要包括位于东区、湾仔区、南区、九龙城区、观塘区、油尖旺区及葵青区十七个地点的九条现有的行人天桥、三条现有的高架行人道及五条现有的行人隧道加建十八座升降机、六条标准斜道和一座楼梯升降机; 与以上相关的土木工程、土力工程、机电工程、现有构筑物的改建工程、道路及渠务工程、及园林美化工程等；及合约内规定的土地勘测工程。</p>','2025-06-04 03:25:06.704000','2025-07-07 07:27:14.715000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',6.00),(130,'vbl9w17l8njpv56hla3c9eoy','土木工程拓展署合约编号CV/2013/08 - 莲塘/香园围口岸土地平整及基建工程 – 工程合约六','土木工程拓展署合约编号CV/2013/08 - 莲塘/香园围口岸土地平整及基建工程 – 工程合约六','土木工程拓展署','2015 年 06 月 24 日 - 2019 年 06 月 21 日','<p>莲塘/香园围口岸是香港、深圳之间第七个陆路口岸。现时文锦渡和沙头角两个陆路口岸，碍于地理限制，难有再扩建的空间。莲塘/香园围口岸位于文锦渡和沙头角之间，正好填补这个不足，使香港与广东省东部地区以至福建及江西的跨境交通连接更方便快捷。新口岸在策略上对推动长远经济发展十分重要。</p><br/><p>兴建一条4.6公里的双程双线分隔主干道以连接沙头角公路交汇处及新口岸，提供排水/排污、水务及新口岸的公共设施工程，另外处理竹园村的迁移，相关的环境缓解措施，以及环境监测及稽核。</p>','2025-06-04 03:26:06.984000','2025-07-07 07:27:14.716000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',7.00),(132,'swrv9tiiii3laeiwe2jjs3lh','香港理工大学-设计及建造合约连接第八期校舍的行人天桥计划','香港理工大学-设计及建造合约连接第八期校舍的行人天桥计划','香港理工大学','2015 年 06 月 15 日 - 2019 年 08 月 29 日','<p>工程主要包括设计和建造连接香港理工大学主校园和第八期校舍的行人天桥。</p><br/><p>主跨度为68米的钢管弓弦结构行人天桥位于漆咸道南。行人道整个宽度约7米而其附属结构由高拉钢悬挂在两个主拱梁上。此行人天桥的美学是根据&quot;飞鱼&quot;概念设计，与周围的标志性建筑互相呼应。</p><br/><p>工程项目包括设计及建造桩地基，桩帽，钢筋混凝土升降机井结构，安装升降机，钢质行人天桥结构及其相关的附属结构，装饰及饰面，楼宇设备，涉及现有的Z座八期的交替及附加的工程的行人天桥连接工</p>','2025-06-04 03:26:58.034000','2025-07-07 07:27:15.073000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',8.00),(134,'svhd49196jt9dcuz3848wg7g','合约编号CV/2014/03无障碍通道设施 — 第一组第一份合约','合约编号CV/2014/03无障碍通道设施 — 第一组第一份合约','土木工程拓展署','2015 年 04 月 13 日 - 2019 年 04 月 12 日','<p>政府一直致力改善公共设施的无障碍程度和可用性，2012年8月，政府启动了「人人畅道通行」（UA）计划，积极在公共通道增设更多无障碍通道设施，例如斜道、升降机和触觉导引路径，以提高公共行人通道的便利性和包容性。</p><br/><p>此项目包括在8个地点(香港岛4个地点，九龙半岛4个地点)设置16部升降机。</p>','2025-06-04 03:27:51.114000','2025-07-07 07:27:18.694000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',9.00),(136,'pmkext2rf0h92unnkgrgtiko','合约编号HY/2013/12屯门至赤鱲角连接路 - 北面连接路收费广场及相关工程','合约编号HY/2013/12屯门至赤鱲角连接路 - 北面连接路收费广场及相关工程\n\n','路政署','2014 年 07 月 21 日 - 2019 年 09 月 21 日','<p>屯门至赤鱲角连接路加强了新界、大屿山、港珠澳大桥与机场之间的连接性。这条新道路可将新界西北至香港国际机场的行车距离缩短最多22公里。屯门至赤鱲角连接路的北部连接路段以隧道连接第屯门40区，而南部连接段则以高架桥连接香港口岸、北大屿山与港珠澳大桥香港口岸。</p><br/><p>此项目工程主要包括建造北部连接路段的收费广场(佔地约5.4公顷)及相关构筑物、行车道和行人天桥，修改屯门龙门路及龙富路的部分行车路段并重新定线和相关工程。</p>','2025-06-04 03:28:40.551000','2025-07-07 07:27:18.592000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',10.00),(138,'rfniiyuhrumlekxfqao5glrf','启德发展计划 - 启德机场北面停机坪第3A期基建工程','启德发展计划 - 启德机场北面停机坪第3A期基建工程\n\n','土木工程拓展署','2013 年 07 月 15 日 - 2017 年 04 月 27 日','<p>项目主要工程包括兴建约长890米的新道路，涵盖L1，L11路和一条连接太子道东与D1路的交流道，一条长约225米的通过部分太子道东的行车路，一条长约205米的新行人隧道，以及现有地铁全长约6000米的延伸段，穿越太子道东，在启德机场北面停机坪和新蒲岗地区改善和扩建现有道路，路灯，交通辅助设施，排水渠，污水渠，水管，美化工程及机电工程，提供环境保护措施，以及执行与上述工程有关的环境监察及审核工作。</p>','2025-06-04 03:29:31.633000','2025-07-07 07:27:18.550000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',11.00),(140,'ogk90ld8bgnm7rqr3hoznxms','沙田至中环线 - 合约编号1108 启德站及相关隧道工程','沙田至中环线 - 合约编号1108 启德站及相关隧道工程\n\n','香港铁路有限公司','2013 年 04 月 25 日 - 2018 年 11 月 18 日','<p>沙中线为政府出资兴建的策略性铁路项目, 提供一条贯穿沙田与中环的走廊. 这是在众多沙中线合约的其中一份. 其合约要求兴建启德站及相关隧道, 这地下车站是由两层的混凝土结构组成. 车站位于启德发展区的中心. 当完工时, 启德市民出外的交通时间将会大大减低, 如过海时间将会大幅减低.</p>','2025-06-04 03:30:16.266000','2025-07-07 07:27:18.514000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',12.00),(142,'wzl02rkahn8tjju37m3j1aih','沙田至中环线 – 合约编号1106 钻石山站扩建工程','沙田至中环线 – 合约编号1106 钻石山站扩建工程\n\n','香港铁路有限公司','2012 年 12 月 17 日 - 2018 年 11 月 18 日','<p>沙中线全长 17 公里, 是一个全港策略性铁路项目，当中设有 10 个车站，钻石山站 是六个转线站中的其中一个。扩建后的钻石山站将会是未来沙中线及现时观塘线的转线站。</p><br/><p>合约编号1106 钻石山站扩建工程除兴建新沙中线大堂及月台外车站亦会增加多项新设施，包括安装3 部新升降机和12 条新扶手电梯，增加自动售票机、自动柜员机和商铺，以及加设公众洗手间等。此外合约内容亦包括搬迁文物结构和考古发掘。</p>','2025-06-04 03:31:10.227000','2025-07-07 07:27:19.903000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',13.00),(144,'e1e012zo41t802qb8lk12ejs','博爱交汇处改善工程','博爱交汇处改善工程\n\n','路政署','2012 年 11 月 30 日 - 2016 年 10 月 15 日','<p>&quot;博爱交汇处改善工程&quot;为路政署于2012年11月展开的 NEC 工程合约，目的为改善博爱交汇处以纾缓现时该交汇处所承受的交通压力，并满足未来的交通需求。 合约内容包括于博爱交汇处一段元朗公路(往九龙方向)增建一条行车天桥﹔建造一段连接支路以连接元朗公路的高架路段与地面路段(往屯门方向)﹔及在博爱迴旋处的引道(近博爱医院)建造一段分隔左转行车道。</p><br/><p>本工程要于原本以繁忙闻名的博爱交汇处的中心及周边建设。 交通改道限制， 狭窄的工作空间及複杂的地下公共线路为本工程的几个重大挑战。</p><br/><p>此外本合约其中一个特色是本合约採用较新式的NEC3工程合约，强调承建商、项目经理及业主的互信及合作、提倡及早解决工程问题与尽早锁定财务风险等等。 本工程的人员都通过今次合约的经验更了解NEC3的优点、行政要求、工作模式及合约重点。为未来政府工程合约的新趋势做好准备。</p>','2025-06-04 03:32:15.522000','2025-07-07 07:27:18.682000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',14.00),(146,'ixo1lg9lfp97o1cky3uxcbh1','香港仔港湾兩岸海滨长廊和鸭脷洲大街 一带之美化工程','香港仔港湾兩岸海滨长廊和鸭脷洲大街 一带之美化工程\n\n','土木工程拓展署','2011 年 09 月 30 日 - 2014 年 12 月 31 日','<p>香港仔两岸海滨长廊和鸭脷洲大街一带之美化工程采用设计与建造合约形式。本工程主旨为改善香港仔两岸的旅游设施，进一步突显香港仔独有的&quot;传统渔港&quot;及本土文化特色，并加强多元化旅游的元素，以提升香港仔对海外旅客及本地居民的吸引力。</p>','2025-06-04 03:33:00.067000','2025-07-07 07:27:18.919000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',15.00),(148,'s6ztf72j6ov9qb0hmqz12ina','为横跨黄竹坑道近业勤街及横跨礼顿道及伊荣街之两条行人天桥，横跨屯门公路近青桃径之行车天桥，及横过百和路近蓬瀛仙馆之行人隧道兴建升降机','为横跨黄竹坑道近业勤街及横跨礼顿道及伊荣街之两条行人天桥，横跨屯门公路近青桃径之行车天桥，及横过百和路近蓬瀛仙馆之行人隧道兴建升降机\n\n','路政署','2011 年 07 月 01 日 - 2014 年 06 月 30 日','<p>政府致力缔造无障碍通行的环境，方便有特殊需要的市民外出。政府多年来一直为行人信道加设无障碍信道设施。但随着本港人口日渐老化，必须加快步伐，增设无障碍通道设施，更利便市民。就此，政府改善现行政策，推出加装升降机的计划，在香港缔造「人人畅道通行」的环境。</p><br/><p>此项目为其一个工程项目，主要包括在两条行人天桥，一条行车天桥及一条行人隧道建造共六部行人升降机，拆除及重建三条楼梯，进行行人天桥/行车天桥/行人隧道的结构修改以及相关的照明设施、排水系统、公用设施迁移及机电工程。</p>','2025-06-04 03:33:53.416000','2025-07-07 07:27:19.200000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',16.00),(150,'bwdb6fkssec3m43xr3g7u5zg','湾仔发展计划第二期 – 横跨港铁荃湾线段的中环湾仔绕道','湾仔发展计划第二期 – 横跨港铁荃湾线段的中环湾仔绕道\n\n','土木工程拓展署','2011 年 01 月 20 日 - 2013 年 07 月 15 日','<p>湾仔发展计划第二期为湾仔北和北角提供土地，用以兴建中环及湾仔绕道和东区走廊连接路。工程将会为新增的土地发展成世界级海滨长廊供市民享用，同时亦有助纾缓湾仔附近一带的交通问题。</p><br/><p>本合约是湾仔发展计划第二期其中一个项目，工程范围包括进行土地平整及兴建横跨港铁荃湾线的中环湾仔绕道隧道。由于绕道隧道跨越现有港铁荃湾线，令工程增添一项重大的限制。我们以场外预制法建造跨越在港铁荃湾线之上的巨型箱形结构，以避免对港铁荃湾线加载负荷。箱形结构物完成后，会以水路拖运至工地安装。这个建造方法既不会影响港铁荃湾线，亦较现场建造符合成本效益。</p>','2025-06-04 03:34:39.657000','2025-07-07 07:27:19.911000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',17.00),(152,'c50maarzg2t80777w8wwnq0w','合约编号HY/2008/12屯门公路巴士转乘站','合约编号HY/2008/12屯门公路巴士转乘站\n\n','路政署','2010 年 07 月 15 日 - 2015 年 07 月 31 日','<p>该项工程主要包括在小榄交汇处附近的屯门公路往九龙方向及在大榄角回旋处附近的屯门公路往屯门方向辟设巴士转乘站，把兄弟桥扩阔，建造一条连接桥，可让乘客步行往来屯门公路及大榄角两个等候处转乘其他巴士线。连接桥上设有两部升降机，方便残障人士往来。另外进行附属工程，包括重建道路、建造上盖、渠务、环境美化、交通辅助设施、街道照明、斜坡、水务等工程及提供相关设施予交通管制监察系统。</p><br/><p>这项工程旨在提供便利的巴士转乘设施，让乘客转乘取道屯门公路往来新界西北的各条巴士线。这项安排既能让现有乘客于转乘站有更多巴士路线的选择，又能大大提升新界西北巴士网络的整体效率，便利乘客，纾缓交通挤塞，以及减低路边空气污染。</p>','2025-06-04 03:35:34.171000','2025-07-07 07:27:19.267000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',18.00),(154,'ksanylsby1q0fdoq7j78dm6c','湾仔发展计划第二期–中环湾仔绕道香港会议展览中心段','湾仔发展计划第二期–中环湾仔绕道香港会议展览中心段\n\n','土木工程拓展署','2009 年 12 月 30 日 - 2016 年 05 月 31 日','<p>湾仔发展计划第二期为湾仔北和北角提供土地，用以兴建中环及湾仔绕道和东区走廊连接路。工程将会为新增的土地发展成世界级海滨长廊供市民享用，同时亦有助纾缓湾仔附近一带的交通问题。</p><br/><p>本合约是湾仔发展计划第二期其中一个项目，工程范围主要包括于香港会议展览中心(会展)两期之间的水道范围内进行土地平整、兴建中环湾仔绕道隧道，以及其他相关工程。</p>','2025-06-04 03:37:07.754000','2025-07-07 07:27:19.884000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',19.00),(156,'qamjwmk44hchbqgd61fpp98o','将军澳进一步发展-将军澳第一期堆填区基础设施工程(第一阶段)设计及建造','将军澳进一步发展-将军澳第一期堆填区基础设施工程(第一阶段)设计及建造\n\n','路政署','2009 年 12 月 29 日 - 2012 年 04 月 03 日','<p>将军澳进一步发展主要改进新市镇的整体设计，把将军澳建设成一个居住环境优越的新市镇。</p><p>本合约是将军澳进一步发展其中一项工程，目的为改善将军澳第一期堆填区与邻近地区的连接，以支持将来堆填区上的康乐发展。项目范围包括沿将军澳第一期堆填区及在将军澳市中心南，兴建一条长约2公里的行人路、约1.6公里的单车径、一条长约140米的行人与单车人士共享的跨水道桥梁及一条长约1公里的草面砖小径及相关景观工程。</p>','2025-06-04 03:38:01.405000','2025-07-07 07:27:18.960000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',20.00),(158,'bzvnzvkndmb787i7wizmy1hn','合约编号KL/2008/09启德发展计划－ 启德机场北面停机坪的基础设施 配合公共房屋及政府合署的首期基建工程','合约编号KL/2008/09启德发展计划－ 启德机场北面停机坪的基础设施 配合公共房屋及政府合署的首期基建工程\n\n','土木工程拓展署','2009 年 07 月 15 日 - 2013 年 08 月 23 日','<p>工程主要包括建造长约2.6公里的新道路，包括工程管制、管理和维修现有道路及将其改道，建造两条行人天桥FB1和FB4，建造相关排水设施包括箱形暗渠、排污设施和供水设施工程，美化和扩展现有行人隧道SW1，美化现有行人隧道SW3和SW5，美化环境工程和纾减环境影响措施。</p><br/><p>工程包括把协调道重新定线，建设区内道路L2，L3，L4（部分）和L15。与道路工程相关的还有相关的街道设施，道路标记和交通标志，横过太子道东的高速公路结构（行人天桥，行人隧道，改善工程）的工程，供应公屋和政府合署的渠务，水务，食水和海水供应系统的建造。工程亦包括在L3公路沿线建造两条箱形排水暗渠BC1及BC2，一条2.5米x 2.5米的箱形排水暗渠，以及分别连接沿L2公路的美化市容地带的现有的明渠二号及3米x2 .8米的箱形排水暗渠及现有的启德明渠，拆卸横跨货运道的机电工程署总部的机电工程署总部斜坡的现有斜坡，放弃现有的明渠1号及喉管，兴建由L2路至行人隧道SW5及宏光道的5条行人通道，康城街及启华街交界处的改善工程，以及为在北面停机坪提供包括公屋及政府合署的早期发展的基建进行机电工程，美化环境工程。</p>','2025-06-04 03:39:02.025000','2025-07-07 07:27:18.907000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',21.00),(160,'ev5wptzssylgtxi09avdxcuz','位于青衣及荃湾引道的青荃桥的隔音屏障加建工程','位于青衣及荃湾引道的青荃桥的隔音屏障加建工程\n\n','路政署','2008 年 01 月 08 日 - 2011 年 07 月 09 日','<p>工程主要包括:</p>','2025-06-04 03:39:59.927000','2025-07-07 07:27:20.743000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',22.00),(162,'yxc9an9zg972pr7bwbm8svyy','商用航空中心扩建工程','商用航空中心扩建工程\n\n','香港机场管理局','2007 年 11 月 16 日 - 2009 年 01 月 25 日','<p>工程包括扩建现有的滑行道Z3和额外的停机位</p>','2025-06-04 03:40:54.216000','2025-07-07 07:27:18.906000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',23.00),(164,'ynubb8bb7x6ytthiocaf8yhh','屯门第18区L18A路道路工程','屯门第18区L18A路道路工程\n\n','土木工程拓展署','2007 年 04 月 30 日 - 2009 年 05 月 29 日','<p>工程的主要项目包括建造一条长约 400米， 宽10.3米的双线行车道并两侧备有3.5米宽行人路; 及1段长约160米横跨皇珠路的高架桥并在桥两侧铺设长约 135米的挡土墙</p>','2025-06-04 03:42:14.968000','2025-07-07 07:27:19.857000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',24.00),(166,'e6e1lsie7d7csj73s4plf5lz','机场中部停机坪改善工程','机场中部停机坪改善工程\n\n','香港机场管理局','2006 年 11 月 23 日 - 2007 年 08 月 05 日','<p>该工程包括制造，供应，施工，安装，测试和设计中部停机坪改善工程</p><br/><p>1. 地盘清扫</p><br/><p>拆除街灯并运送到储存仓</p><br/><p>拆除滑行道边灯并运送到储存仓</p><br/><p>2. 机场道面铺设工程</p><br/><p>土方工程，沥青路面，雨水排水系统，电话电讯管道挖掘及电缆布设工程及安装停机坪标志</p><br/><p>3. 高桅照明装置</p><br/><p>地基，桅杆和相关的电缆和照明设备</p><br/><p>4. 系统工程</p><br/><p>紧急电话系统，闪电预警系统，接地保护活动区域指引标志及先进的监控和数据收集系统</p><br/>','2025-06-04 03:47:47.944000','2025-07-07 07:27:20.887000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',25.00),(168,'cnpq2xpuaxq1tovwm9avh2qa','屯门第38区环保园发展工程','屯门第38区环保园发展工程\n\n','环境保护署','2006 年 07 月 03 日 - 2010 年 01 月 01 日','<p>环保园是一个关键因素的战略，其目的是促进本地循环再造业和快速激活一个可持续发展的经济提供长期的土地设施的环境及循环再造业。通过鼓励和促进再利用，回收和循环再造的废物资源，并返回他们的消费循环中，环保园将有助于利用的潜力本地循环再造业，减轻沉重的需求，香港的堆填区。</p><br/><p>环保园占地 20公顷的土地位于屯门第38区，将分两个阶段发展。环保园第一期（约 8公顷），将用于对结束占领和2006年第二期（约 12公顷）在2009年。各种环保设施正在使用首次在香港，如太阳管道，太阳能水龙头，并且有绿色屋顶等等</p>','2025-06-04 03:48:42.977000','2025-07-07 07:27:19.964000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',26.00),(170,'ankk45kp6lyyrdwc0nnipq5s','元朗及锦田污水收集系统及污水排放设施建造工程','元朗及锦田污水收集系统及污水排放设施建造工程\n\n','渠务署','2005 年 12 月 29 日 - 2010 年 06 月 30 日','<p>该工程包括：</p><br/>','2025-06-04 03:50:03.616000','2025-07-07 07:27:19.651000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',27.00),(172,'je31jm08wdtmsphgvj40zrck','香港国际机场跑道灯号迁移工程','香港国际机场跑道灯号迁移工程\n\n','香港机场管理局','2005 年 07 月 19 日 - 2006 年 04 月 09 日','<p>整个安装工程需在夜间进行以减少对机场运作的影响。由于工程时间紧凑，故需精心策划详细的施工进度计划，使晚上的生产力发挥至最大。虽然劳动工作只能在夜间进行，但工程筹划小组仍需要24小时投入到项目团队里。</p><br/><p>预制混凝土地基（在白天预制）是非常适合用作快速安装杆照明系统上。</p><br/><p>机场地面照明系统的变压器装置需由美国直接进口，以满足严格的机场用途要求。</p>','2025-06-04 03:50:50.501000','2025-07-07 07:27:20.076000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',28.00),(174,'bywxif1oi4oonaudsn1d2u7t','香港国际机场航天城停车场工程','香港国际机场航天城停车场工程\n\n','香港机场管理局','2005 年 05 月 31 日 - 2005 年 12 月 20 日','<p>我们公司是香港第一间应用GFA铺面物的公司。GFA是混合颗粒材枓和&#x27;粉煤灰&#x27;或煤灰。GFA是一种需缓慢硬化的混合体，在短期内是一个未绑定的材料，需较长的处理时间，但中至长期的结构表现与惯用的材料一样，如沥青。</p><br/><p>GFA是煤发电的副产废物，是一种合乎经济和环保供选择的铺面物。</p>','2025-06-04 03:51:58.140000','2025-07-07 07:27:19.944000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',29.00),(176,'pc4n03cenj4oiz16i81ljg32','粉岭公路近上水彩园村及粉岭中心的隔音屏障工程','粉岭公路近上水彩园村及粉岭中心的隔音屏障工程\n\n','路政署','2004 年 08 月 23 日 - 2006 年 03 月 20 日','<p>该项工程主要包括沿粉岭公路建造约 600米长的直立式隔音屏障及约2400米长的悬臂式隔音屏障。</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-04 03:52:39.631000','2025-07-07 07:27:20.686000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',30.00),(178,'gafydbcmnv7ma7iqby0xbvas','白石角发展计划基础设施工程 - 第 2A 阶段','白石角发展计划基础设施工程 - 第 2A 阶段\n\n','土木工程拓展署','2004 年 06 月 29 日 - 2008 年 10 月 15 日','<p>白石角发展计划基础设施工程 主要工程项目包括地盘平整工程，以及道路和桥梁建设，自行车道，海滨长廊，人行隧道，及相关的环境美化工程等</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-04 03:53:22.307000','2025-07-07 07:27:20.421000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',31.00),(180,'nvl67w3caub7g6wwb69b9kj1','铜锣湾行车天桥重建及相关的维园道扩阔工程 (合约编号：HY/2003/27)','铜锣湾行车天桥重建及相关的维园道扩阔工程\n\n','路政署','2004 年 06 月 10 日 - 2008 年 05 月 29 日','<p>工 程 计 划 包 括:</p><br/>','2025-06-04 03:54:17.977000','2025-07-07 07:27:33.213000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',32.00),(182,'wk0ju997hqc1owoxzioqwhm9','沙田新市镇第II阶段 土木工程 – 沙田及马鞍山','沙田新市镇第II阶段 土木工程 – 沙田及马鞍山\n\n','拓展署','2004 年 03 月 26 日 - 2006 年 11 月 18 日','<p>项目包括沙田及马鞍山区内土木工程项目并特别针对于斜坡，道路及渠务工程。由于涉及交通不便的地区，我们采用了崭新的施工方法。 如在多石村后山山上建造一条120米长围栏，我们利用了直升机运送围栏组件到现场及使用特殊设计滑轮系统利用人力安装整个围栏。在修葺2公里长马鞍山海滨长廊时，我们利用陆地及海上机械设备来运输及放置防波堤石。避免对邻近海堤附近的居民做成滋扰，我们在施工过程中应用不同环境的预防措施及与市民建立良好的沟通系统。</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-04 03:55:00.011000','2025-07-07 07:27:24.266000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',33.00),(184,'oxi8q3yanp5gv1tl8bn8b7xl','香港国际机场货运停机坪扩建工程','香港国际机场货运停机坪扩建工程\n\n','香港机场管理局','2004 年 03 月 24 日 - 2005 年 05 月 31 日','<p>工程地点在高度敏感范围，令进出地盘成为一个重大障碍。基于保安理由，每辆进出地盘的车辆都需要接受检查及护送进出地盘。</p><br/><p>在机场跑道旁边运送混凝土令施工上有很大的限制。因此特制了混凝土配料设备。此工程对铺设路面的混凝土有严格的质量要求，需从德国进口，以达到非常精确的混凝土路面。</p>','2025-06-04 03:55:41.891000','2025-07-07 07:27:20.818000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',34.00),(186,'f7hjm4iw47x99ip8ew5pxhcy','罗湖站改善工程：一号至三号站台，连接桥及车站大堂','罗湖站改善工程：一号至三号站台，连接桥及车站大堂\n\n','九广铁路公司','2002 年 11 月 18 日 - 2004 年 07 月 30 日','<p>本项目内所有工程，都是在紧贴现有火车路轨旁或在其上进行。而罗湖站连接罗湖关口，为香港通往深圳最重要的通道。每日人流量超过十万人次，而在节日和主要假期，人流更高达每日三十万人次。其繁忙程度，可以想见。为确保铁路、车站以及关口的正常运作，以免影响正常使用的人士，承建商采取了相应的安全操施及安排，其中包括：大量的工程项目改在晚间，即火车服务停止后进行；提供大量而且稳固的栏栅及工台等用来隔开工程进行的范围和火车的服务范围；实施有效的安全工作程序包括路轨守望员等以确保列车及罗湖站的运作不受工程影响。</p>','2025-06-04 03:56:59.873000','2025-07-07 07:27:20.238000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',35.00),(188,'ekoqurim07t8yj4gg0r319y0','朗屏站公众运输交汇处','朗屏站公众运输交汇处\n\n','九广铁路','2002 年 09 月 23 日 - 2003 年 10 月 11 日','<p>为配合西铁线的发展，原鱼类批发市场的地点更改用途为兴建公共运输交汇处。集团于2002年获得此发展项目，工程主要包括在西铁朗屏站以南兴建一个无盖的公众运输交汇处，供小巴和的士使用，当中包括土木、建筑、园林绿化及屋宇设备等工程，同时也包括土方、挡土墙、道路、行人路、渠务、公用设施转移，围网及修饰等相关工程。其他工程包括建造一段行人天桥、楼梯、升降机及自动扶梯与其上盖结构、在郎屏北的公众运输交汇处外围兴建新的道路和行人路、供应及安装于元朗泵房内更换的药水剂量设备、拆卸邻近元朗泵房的旧渠务署人员宿舍、兴建有照明的有盖行人信道、在专线小巴、巴士、的士站兴建行人侯车亭及改善青山公路旁的行人路和单车径。</p>','2025-06-04 03:57:57.166000','2025-07-07 07:27:29.480000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',36.00),(190,'okutbbkp6pb617bgd5ijx6rx',' 合約編號HY/2016/05 連接荃灣廣場、灣景廣場及毗鄰環境美化地帶之行人天橋','合約編號HY/2016/05 連接荃灣廣場、灣景廣場及毗鄰環境美化地帶之行人天橋','路政署','2017 年 05 月 08 日 - 2019 年 12 月 03 日','<p>本項目主要包括興建一條長約66米、淨闊度約3.5米的有蓋行人天橋，以連接荃灣廣場、灣景廣場及毗鄰環境美化地帶；在海盛路建造1部升降機及一條有蓋樓梯； 重建現有一段在海盛路的停車處以及進行附屬工程，包括相關的道路、渠務、公用設施、公共照明、環境美化、機電系統等工程。</p>','2025-06-04 03:59:22.600000','2025-07-07 07:27:22.947000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',2.00),(192,'paliv0bw4psuooea8t1gvp0z','屯门站公众运输交汇处 ','屯门站公众运输交汇处\n\n','九广铁路','2002 年 09 月 23 日 - 2003 年 08 月 31 日','<p>主要工程包括:</p><br/><p>- 路面</p><br/><p>- 排水渠系统</p><br/><p>- 交通及道路标志</p><br/><p>- 路面标记</p><br/><p>- 栏杆</p><br/><p>- 街道照明设备</p><br/><p>- 有棚的候车 亭</p><br/><p>此工程涉及大量与其它西铁承建商、政府部门及公用事业的交接。为确保工程能顺利、依期完成，我司与上述各有关单位及九广铁路公司的相关人员，进行了紧密的协调及合作，终能顺利完成任务。</p>','2025-06-04 03:59:48.873000','2025-07-07 07:27:23.370000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',37.00),(194,'u0j4qet5qfhovz47k2j3lpgn','合約編號HY/2016/04 將軍澳唐明街與唐德街之間的高架行人道','合約編號HY/2016/04 將軍澳唐明街與唐德街之間的高架行人道路政署','路政署','2016 年 12 月 30 日 - 2021 年 03 月 03 日','<p>此工程主要目的是興建一條高架行人道，連接現時橫跨唐明街的行人天橋至港鐵將軍澳站上蓋之商場及在高架行人道近唐德街建造一部升降機以提供一條舒適和便捷的通道，方便將軍澳市中心一帶的居民(特別是長者)往來。此外，為增加區内可供居民使用的單車泊位數量，進行唐明街現有單車停泊處的重建及擴建工程。興建一條長約一百八十米、淨闊度約五米的高架行人道，連接現時橫跨唐明街的行人天橋至港鐵將軍澳站上蓋之商場；在擬議高架行人道近唐德街建造一部升降機； 重建及擴建現有單車停泊處；以及進行附屬工程，包括相關的道路、渠務、公用設施、公共照明、環境美化、機電系統等工程。</p>','2025-06-04 04:00:33.460000','2025-07-07 07:27:23.367000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',3.00),(196,'mr3copy4z6t7cbtnl3n2lmd0','祁临高速公路','祁临高速公路\n\n','山西省祁临高速公路有限公司','2001 年 04 月 01 日 - 2002 年 11 月 30 日','<p>祁临高速公路位于祁县至临汾市，长度177.72公里，位于山西中南部省。 路面宽度为28.50米，其中北部和南部分别可容纳3条行车道。祁临高速公路是省内高速公路的主干一部分。主干从大棠市到运城市总长666公里，从北到南跨越全省。 它也是第一个该省的高速公路项目通过亚洲开发银行提供资金。</p><br/><p>省政府把全段祁临高速公路分为18个合同标段独立招标，集团为16合同段的承建人。项目为一条长14.3公里，宽28米的沥青混凝土路面公路建设工程。</p><br/><p>本合同于2001年6月底动工，在施工期间，我方积极协调分包单位及我方的施工力量，维持每天工时不少于13个小时，务求补偿被缩减的18个月工期。最终，本合同段工程于2002年12月底完工，工程质量超越国家及省政府要求，获省政府多次表扬。</p>','2025-06-04 04:00:39.768000','2025-07-07 07:27:25.558000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',38.00),(198,'u8strrdht55i9bpbp0huz0hl','南昌站','南昌站\n\n','九广铁路','1999 年 10 月 01 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>南昌站作为西铁第一期的南面总站，是西铁及地铁东涌线的共享综合车站。车站的构造，不仅覆盖了现有的西九龙高架高速公路及机场快线、地铁东涌线，同时，也包括了相关的连接行车道路与高架桥梁系统。另外，在车站建设施工期间，要保持西九龙高架高速公路、机场快线及东涌线正常运作的要求，为施工带来了不少难度。因此，对施工的技术要求是非常高和严格的。</p><br/><p>本车站设有地面沿车轨站台，以及与地铁东涌线共用的地底车站大堂。该大堂建于正在营运中的机场铁路及东涌线的地底。为确保机场铁路及东涌线正常运作，所以特别选择以「从上而下」（top-down）的建筑方式兴建，其规模在香港实属罕见。地底车站大堂及站台设计配合地下空间进行最大限度的开发及利用，减少占用地面的空间，也确保外观的宏伟。在提供商业活动的同时，也利于乘客流向的疏导，凭借高效人流引导设计迅速将乘客引导至最近的机场快线车站、公共汽车站、住宅及商业区。</p><br/><p>为配合将来在车站顶棚会建筑多幢多层式的住宅物业及高层商业大厦，车站的梁、柱结构及其基础的设计作出了相应的预备工作，其基础包括多种不同类型的椿基：如大口径现浇钢筋混凝土搅拌椿、地下连续墙及打入式工字型钢椿等等。车站施工期间，在车站顶部预留了大楼底层的钢筋混凝土柱结构。将来上盖物业发展时，站顶平台会以平板多肢结构承托上盖的多层剪力墙，这对将来顶棚以上的楼宇设计时产生的任何变动，是一个弹性的处理方法。</p>','2025-06-04 04:01:32.591000','2025-07-07 07:27:31.341000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',39.00),(200,'w32pwoy5e05gnv4u558bvxu3','合約編號KL/2015/03啟德發展計劃－前北面停機坪第3B期基礎設施','合約編號KL/2015/03啟德發展計劃－前北面停機坪第3B期基礎設施','土木工程拓展署','2016 年 12 月 22 日 - 2022 年 01 月 31 日','<p>本項目包括建造一段雙行雙車線道路L2、一座跨越太子道東的高架行人通道LW4，以及一條連接啟德發展區與彩虹邨的180米長行人隧道SW4(使用無開挖法技術)。</p><p>項目採用香港首部矩形隧道鑽挖機(RTBM) ，可增強工程安全性，並更有效管控隧道施工風險。此外，使用在場外預製場生產預製隧道主體結構，不但能提升工程質量，也為工人提供更安全的工作環境。</p>','2025-06-04 04:01:51.741000','2025-07-07 07:27:24.159000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',4.00),(202,'h9ybmppcamssotnno4ut2l2j','美孚站','美孚站\n\n\n','九广铁路公司','1999 年 08 月 02 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>美孚站位于荔枝角公园内，采用密封式设计。其设计特色在于使车站与公园环境融为一体。车站的天台设计为空中花园，其中包括园林绿化及各种休闲设施，为邻近的大型高密度住宅区如美孚新村及清丽苑等的居民提供服务。本站的整体设计及建造，均以融入相邻居民区与环境为主题。例如：提供足够的人行道及车道从车站通往邻近的住宅区等。在建筑期间减低对居民的影响，也是一个重要的事项。所以，在建筑期间，专门修建了一条临时人行天桥横跨整个工地，为居民提供方便的来往通道。工程完成后，由于西铁的通车，美孚站及其天台上的空中花园的建成启用，大幅改善了邻近地区的交通及环境，居民的生活质素也得到相应提高。</p>','2025-06-04 04:02:27.408000','2025-07-07 07:27:20.985000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',40.00),(204,'g1jdkfcuf1q8799viocgiyfm',' 合約編號NE/2015/02將軍澳－藍田隧道－主要幹路P2及相關工程','合約編號NE/2015/02將軍澳－藍田隧道－主要幹路P2及相關工程','土木工程拓展署','2016 年 07 月 29 日 - 2023 年 09 月 28 日','<p>將軍澳 - 藍田隧道(將藍隧道)旨在應對將軍澳持續發展所帶來的日益增加的對外交通需求。將藍隧道連同擬建的T2主幹路和中九龍幹線，將形成連接西九龍和將軍澳的東西行快速公路六號幹線。</p><p>本項目屬將藍隧道的一部分，涉及建造一條長 800米的雙程雙線分隔公路(P2路)。其中約600米為低於地面行車道, 其中約200米以綠化平台覆蓋。項目還包括相關的填海、土木、結構、海事、電力、機械、環境綠化、環境保護和緩解措施的配套工程。</p>','2025-06-04 04:03:01.527000','2025-07-07 07:27:30.173000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',5.00),(206,'b32fc2g4poonhn8jqmomazns','土木及基础工程','土木及基础工程\n\n','九广铁路','1999 年 07 月 02 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>该合约包括西铁车厂及锦田站的建造、安装，土木及基建的设计。该工程包括所有地盘平整、渠务、道路、公用设施、环境美化、主要排水渠道及轨道路基平整工程。这些道路工程包括兴建一条约660米长的双程高架桥横跨地盘、消防通道和公共通道、停车场及道路交汇处设施。</p>','2025-06-04 04:03:29.782000','2025-07-07 07:27:27.578000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',41.00),(208,'g5kn1vr2d2l77q59m3f3wavs',' 合約編號 HY/2014/18無障礙通道設施 - 第三期第七份合約','合約編號 HY/2014/18無障礙通道設施 - 第三期第七份合約','路政署','2015 年 11 月 25 日 - 2019 年 11 月 25 日','<p>政府一直致力為公共行人通道加建無障礙通道設施，於2012年8月推出「人人暢道通行」計劃，積極增設更多無障礙通道設施，方便市民上落公共行人通道。</p><p>此工程主要包括位於東區、灣仔區、南區、九龍城區、觀塘區、油尖旺區及葵青區十七個地點的九條現有的行人天橋、三條現有的高架行人道及五條現有的行人隧道加建十八座升降機、六條標準斜道和一座樓梯升降機; 與以上相關的土木工程、土力工程、機電工程、現有構築物的改建工程、道路及渠務工程、及園林美化工程等；及合約內規定的土地勘測工程。</p>','2025-06-04 04:04:11.745000','2025-07-07 07:27:31.470000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',6.00),(210,'ohp4jq2qktwgy9k64dtde3in','薄扶林道及沙孙道交通交汇处','薄扶林道及沙孙道交通交汇处\n\n','路政署','1998 年 12 月 16 日 - 2003 年 03 月 31 日','<p>本项目的重点为扩阔一段在全港规模最大，最主要的玛丽医院前的薄扶林道与及改善其邻近的路口，提供一个畅通无阻的交汇处。确保紧急车辆能够尽快进出医院，也改善附近一带地区的交通流量。在扩阔薄扶林道的部份，工程包括在陡峭的斜坡上建造一段高架行车道。同时，也包括把现有的薄扶林道拉直及重建。并重建沙孙道及薄扶林道路口。此外，本项目也包括以重建的沙孙道为起点，建造一条连接玛丽医院的连接桥。重建班士尼道与薄扶林道路口。其部份路面也是于斜坡上兴建的高架行车道。由于大部份的高架行车道的结构工程都是在陡峭的斜坡上进行，工程的难度大大的提高。尤其是在进行基础工程的阶段。为建造现浇搅拌桩承建商采用了大规模的临时工作台及在斜坡上开挖的临时平台。薄扶林道为连接港岛西区及南区的其中一条主要通道，交通流量非常高，车速又快。于工程进行期间，为确保交通安全及畅顺，承建商提供了大量的相关操施，包括：建造临时扩阔路面，提供及安装大量的交通标置，指示及照明系统等。</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-04 04:04:37.385000','2025-07-07 07:27:36.219000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',42.00),(212,'olm2l30d5ztadkpk07dg11ms',' 土木工程拓展署合約編號CV/2013/08 - 蓮塘/香園圍口岸土地平整及基建工程 – 工程合約六','土木工程拓展署合約編號CV/2013/08 - 蓮塘/香園圍口岸土地平整及基建工程 – 工程合約六','土木工程拓展署','2015 年 06 月 24 日 - 2019 年 06 月 21 日','<p>蓮塘/香園圍口岸是香港、深圳之間第七個陸路口岸。現時文錦渡和沙頭角兩個陸路口岸，礙於地理限制，難有再擴建的空間。蓮塘/香園圍口岸位於文錦渡和沙頭角之間，正好填補這個不足，使香港與廣東省東部地區以至福建及江西的跨境交通連接更方便快捷。新口岸在策略上對推動長遠經濟發展十分重要。</p><p>興建一條4.6公里的雙程雙線分隔主幹道以連接沙頭角公路交匯處及新口岸，提供排水/排污、水務及新口岸的公共設施工程，另外處理竹園村的遷移，相關的環境緩解措施，以及環境監測及稽核。</p>','2025-06-04 04:05:36.746000','2025-07-07 07:27:21.489000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',7.00),(214,'k9jus5084926nj7yb1l91skq','屯门公路改善工程 – 大榄段','屯门公路改善工程 – 大榄段\n\n','路政署','1998 年 09 月 01 日 - 2001 年 05 月 31 日','<p>屯门公路是連接屯门和九龍的主要道路。这项工程旨在为屯门公路大榄段现有的东行车道提供一条爬坡车道和硬路肩 ，并改善屯门公路上的斜坡。</p><br/><p>本项目的其中一个重点为于屯门公路北侧之岩石斜坡上进行开挖。为使开挖能安全地进行，不至影向斜坡下繁忙的交通，我司把公路南侧邻近兄弟桥的山坡削平，建造临时车道，把屯门公路东、西向的行车线南移，远离开挖进行的工地。同时，我司又调动施工的次序，先于分隔东西行车线的路中斜坡上，建造强化填料护土墙及新增的永久行车线，把东行的行车线南移，远离北面的斜坡，腾出空间，于路旁建造临时防滚石网及铺设沙软垫，以防止于斜坡开挖时松脱的石块，滚下斜坡，对路过的车辆构成危险。</p><br/><p>项目的另一重点为于分隔东西行车线的路中斜坡上设计及建造强化填料护土墙以兴建一条新增的永久行车线。建造该段强化填料护土墙包括于斜坡上进行开挖。开挖期间，以临时迷你桩墙枝撑东行车道的路基。建造护土墙的工序包括浇注钢筋混凝土地基，于地基上按装预制钢筋混凝土构件，于构件背后分层回填、压实及按装特别填料及经热浸镀锌处理的钢制强化筋。为进行此部份之工程，我司特别设计及建造了一条钢结构临时桥，从青山公路旁的工地至位于分隔屯门公路东西行线的路中斜坡的工地，横跨青山公路及屯门公路西行线，以便运送材料、机械、工具及人员行返工地。</p><br/><p>在整个项目进行过程中，要碓保屯门公路东行之三条行车线畅通无阻。为进行重建现有的路面，我司设计及执行了一个极为复杂、多阶段的逐行车线交通改道计划。重建路面得以顺利完成，并没有对交通构成重大影向。</p>','2025-06-04 04:05:38.281000','2025-07-07 07:27:20.777000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',43.00),(216,'yobkjbk6hk0fvd73a5ys54n6','大埔发展项目第12及39区场地平整工程','大埔发展项目第12及39区场地平整工程\n\n','拓展署','1998 年 03 月 18 日 - 2003 年 05 月 05 日','<p>建造长1.6公里的主干道和长7.3公里直径600厘米的水管及相关工程。这些工程包括：</p>','2025-06-04 04:06:51.992000','2025-07-07 07:27:23.704000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',44.00),(218,'c7f3f41s6cd9jfkwz723cagv','九龙观塘康宁道公园第一期建造工程','九龙观塘康宁道公园第一期建造工程\n\n','建筑署','1997 年 04 月 11 日 - 1999 年 03 月 26 日','<br/>','2025-06-04 04:08:15.466000','2025-07-07 07:27:22.212000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',45.00),(220,'phwxphr7eebv3ikl07cqjn1q','新田农村防洪工程','新田农村防洪工程\n\n','渠务署','1996 年 11 月 20 日 - 2000 年 12 月 26 日','<p>本项目之重点工程是乘托于筏式基础上的泵房及其相关的洪水储水池塘。本项目还包括建造围绕新田村的长约1.74公里的围堤及于围堤上建造的1.35米宽的车道。</p><br/><p>新田村一带地区的洪水会流经一系列之沙井及沟渠，进入与泵房相连的储水池塘。当塘内洪水的水位升至预设之水位时，泵房的5漕抽水系统便会激活，把洪水经由双孔箱形暗渠输送到深圳河的下游。</p><br/><p>为确保流经新田村至深圳河的河流不受影向，工程期间进行了一系列的临时河流改道。</p><br/><p>围堤的设计从内至外为：一般填土、碎石层、混凝土衬层。最后在斜坡面铺设预制混凝土草砖。草砖有特别开孔设计以供喷草。个别草砖之间也互相扣紧，承受洪水涨退的影响。</p><br/><p>本项目的主要困难是在建造泵房基础时，处理从邻近的渔塘流进的地下水。同时，用于建造围堤的工作空间非常有限，给施工队伍带来很大的挑战。施工队以钢板桩建造临时围堰，以有效地控制流进基础范围的地下水。</p>','2025-06-04 04:09:20.796000','2025-07-07 07:27:20.890000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',46.00),(222,'ifx8gerp1ksxadw3srdqdumt',' 香港理工大學-設計及建造合約連接第八期校舍的行人天橋計劃','香港理工大學-設計及建造合約連接第八期校舍的行人天橋計劃','香港理工大學','2015 年 06 月 15 日 - 2019 年 08 月 29 日','<p>工程主要包括設計和建造連接香港理工大學主校園和第八期校舍的行人天橋。</p><p>主跨度為68米的鋼管弓弦結構行人天橋位於漆咸道南。行人道整個寬度約7米而其附屬結構由高拉鋼懸掛在兩個主拱樑上。此行人天橋的美學是根據“飛魚”概念設計，與周圍的標誌性建築互相呼應。</p><p>工程項目包括設計及建造樁地基，樁帽，鋼筋混凝土升降機井結構，安裝升降機，鋼質行人天橋結構及其相關的附屬結構，裝飾及飾面，樓宇設備，涉及現有的Z座八期的交替及附加的工程的行人天橋連接工程。</p>','2025-06-04 04:09:36.389000','2025-07-07 07:27:26.316000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',8.00),(224,'mpk48sp1k1gjl4yzql4jabn3','屯门38区内河货柜码头','屯门38区内河货柜码头\n\n','内河码头有限公司','1996 年 11 月 01 日 - 1999 年 11 月 30 日','<p>主要工程包括：</p><br/>','2025-06-04 04:10:24.362000','2025-07-07 07:27:30.154000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',47.00),(226,'rzirmkl5r1aqya810ptkt7cf','合約編號CV/2014/03無障礙通道設施 — 第一組第一份合約','合約編號CV/2014/03無障礙通道設施 — 第一組第一份合約','土木工程拓展署','2015 年 04 月 13 日 - 2019 年 04 月 12 日','<p>政府一直致力改善公共設施的無障礙程度和可用性，2012年8月，政府啟動了「人人暢道通行」（UA）計劃，積極在公共通道增設更多無障礙通道設施，例如斜道、升降機和觸覺導引路徑，以提高公共行人通道的便利性和包容性。</p><p>此項目包括在8個地點(香港島4個地點，九龍半島4個地點)設置16部升降機。</p>','2025-06-04 04:10:34.253000','2025-07-07 07:27:21.552000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',9.00),(228,'cwjiqzcw52ke77150v3ar5ji','望后石垃圾堆填区 合约G标段 – 卫生堆填及有关工程','望后石垃圾堆填区 合约G标段 – 卫生堆填及有关工程\n\n','土木工程署','1996 年 05 月 01 日 - 1997 年 09 月 30 日','<p>这个工程是望后石垃圾堆填工程最后一期工程。</p><br/><p>工程內容主要包括：</p><br/><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>收纳及处理堆填区内的固体废弃物</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>开挖和清除泥土和石头</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>排水和道路工程</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>铺设水泥</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>地下排水沟及排水网</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>植被工程</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>环境监测工程</li></ul>','2025-06-04 04:11:41.108000','2025-07-07 07:27:28.786000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',48.00),(230,'gcp9z2g3egkv939bk4yo3pi1','合約編號HY/2013/12屯門至赤鱲角連接路 - 北面連接路收費廣場及相關工程','合約編號HY/2013/12屯門至赤鱲角連接路 - 北面連接路收費廣場及相關工程','路政署','2014 年 07 月 21 日 - 2019 年 09 月 21 日','<p>屯門至赤鱲角連接路加強了新界、大嶼山、港珠澳大橋與機場之間的連接性。這條新道路可將新界西北至香港國際機場的行車距離縮短最多22公里。屯門至赤鱲角連接路的北部連接路段以隧道連接第屯門40區，而南部連接段則以高架橋連接香港口岸、北大嶼山與港珠澳大橋香港口岸。</p><p>此項目工程主要包括建造北部連接路段的收費廣場(佔地約5.4公頃)及相關構築物、行車道和行人天橋，修改屯門龍門路及龍富路的部分行車路段並重新定線和相關工程。</p>','2025-06-04 04:11:44.298000','2025-07-07 07:27:30.633000',NULL,8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',10.00),(232,'vdbrxddnr3bycj596e6gpz3e','屯门 38区特别工业区发展 – 填海、海堤、道路、水道','屯门 38区特别工业区发展 – 填海、海堤、道路、水道\n\n','土木工程拓展署','1995 年 09 月 01 日 - 2000 年 01 月 31 日','<p>这项工程包括建造450m长垂直海墙、1000m 长碎石斜坡海墙、建造625m长4 组排水暗渠与道路、污水道、排水道、食水管道和填海28公顷。</p>','2025-06-04 04:12:39.138000','2025-07-07 07:27:29.838000',NULL,15,36,'zh-CN',49.00),(234,'iip1d0z0squ37p1bwmcaojd3','大屿山与机场铁路小蚝湾车厂第一期','大屿山与机场铁路小蚝湾车厂第一期\n\n','地下铁路公司','1995 年 01 月 01 日 - 1998 年 05 月 31 日','<p>本工程为新机场核心工程之一部份，所以准时完成工程十分重要。车厂主楼能够准时完工是本次成功的重要因素。</p><br/><p>由于项目包括多种不同类别之工程，