:33.478000','2025-07-07 07:27:36.184000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',35.00),(585,'do4xrwqjxt7t5keoh00zjw70','沙田至中環線 - 合約編號1108 啟德站及相關隧道工程','沙田至中環線 - 合約編號1108 啟德站及相關隧道工程','香港鐵路有限公司','2013 年 04 月 25 日 - 2018 年 11 月 18 日','<p>沙中線為政府出資興建的策略性鐵路項目, 提供一條貫穿沙田與中環的走廊. 這是在眾多沙中線合約的其中一份. 其合約要求興建啟德站及相關隧道, 這地下車站是由兩層的混凝土結構組成. 車站位於啟德發展區的中心. 當完工時, 啟德市民出外的交通時間將會大大減低, 如過海時間將會大幅減低.</p>','2025-06-04 04:15:33.080000','2025-07-07 07:27:36.191000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.230000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',12.00),(586,'ksbuurm7y04vhbyl325n7u99','商用航空中心擴建工程','商用航空中心擴建工程\n\n','香港機場管理局','2007 年 11 月 16 日 - 2009 年 01 月 25 日','<p>工程包括擴建現有的滑行道Z3和額外的停機位</p>','2025-06-04 05:58:55.906000','2025-07-07 07:27:36.051000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.261000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',25.00),(587,'ohp4jq2qktwgy9k64dtde3in','薄扶林道及沙孙道交通交汇处','薄扶林道及沙孙道交通交汇处\n\n','路政署','1998 年 12 月 16 日 - 2003 年 03 月 31 日','<p>本项目的重点为扩阔一段在全港规模最大，最主要的玛丽医院前的薄扶林道与及改善其邻近的路口，提供一个畅通无阻的交汇处。确保紧急车辆能够尽快进出医院，也改善附近一带地区的交通流量。在扩阔薄扶林道的部份，工程包括在陡峭的斜坡上建造一段高架行车道。同时，也包括把现有的薄扶林道拉直及重建。并重建沙孙道及薄扶林道路口。此外，本项目也包括以重建的沙孙道为起点，建造一条连接玛丽医院的连接桥。重建班士尼道与薄扶林道路口。其部份路面也是于斜坡上兴建的高架行车道。由于大部份的高架行车道的结构工程都是在陡峭的斜坡上进行，工程的难度大大的提高。尤其是在进行基础工程的阶段。为建造现浇搅拌桩承建商采用了大规模的临时工作台及在斜坡上开挖的临时平台。薄扶林道为连接港岛西区及南区的其中一条主要通道，交通流量非常高，车速又快。于工程进行期间，为确保交通安全及畅顺，承建商提供了大量的相关操施，包括：建造临时扩阔路面，提供及安装大量的交通标置，指示及照明系统等。</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-04 04:04:37.385000','2025-07-07 07:27:36.219000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.322000',15,36,'zh-CN',42.00),(588,'xdmrwuuf2mylmo1nx132fuu7','銅鑼灣行車天橋重建及相關的維園道擴闊工程','銅鑼灣行車天橋重建及相關的維園道擴闊工程\n\n','路政署','2004 年 06 月 10 日 - 2008 年 05 月 29 日','<p>工 程 計 劃 包 括:</p><br/>','2025-06-04 06:07:03.586000','2025-07-07 07:27:36.609000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.378000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',34.00),(589,'fbf1zqf09vzakk9m0jx9lo67','羅湖站改善工程：一號至三號月臺，連接橋及車站大堂','羅湖站改善工程：一號至三號月臺，連接橋及車站大堂\n\n','九廣鐵路公司','2002 年 11 月 18 日 - 2004 年 07 月 30 日','<p>本專案內所有工程，都是在緊貼現有火車路軌旁或以上進行。而羅湖站側連接羅湖關口，爲香港通往深圳最重要的通道。每日人流超過十萬人次，而在節日或主要假期，人流更高達三十萬人次。其繁忙情度，可以想見。爲確保鐵路，車站以至關口的運作正常，以免影響使用的人士，承建商採取了相應的安全操施及安排，其中包括了：大量的工程項目改在晚間，當火車服務停止後進行；提供大量而又穩固的欄柵及工台等以分格工程進行的範圍及火車的服務範圍；實施有效的安全工作程式包括路軌守望員等以確保列車及羅湖站的運作不受工程進行影響。</p>','2025-06-04 06:09:18.036000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.317000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.532000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',37.00),(590,'i526d96g10g99h5xtm8wboi8','朗屏站公眾運輸交彙處','朗屏站公眾運輸交彙處\n\n','九廣鐵路','2002 年 09 月 23 日 - 2003 年 10 月 11 日','<p>為配合西鐵綫的發展，原魚類批發市場的地點更改用途為興建公共運輸交匯處。集團於2002年獲得此發展項目，工程主要包括在西鐵朗屏站以南興建一個無蓋的公衆運輸交匯處，供小巴和的士使用，當中包括土木、建築、園林綠化及屋宇設備等工程，同時也包括土方、擋土牆、道路、行人路、渠務、公用設施轉移，圍網及修飾等相關工程。其他工程包括建造一段行人天橋、樓梯、升降機及自動扶梯與其上蓋結構、在郎屏北的公衆運輸交匯處週邊興建新的道路和行人路、供應及安裝於元朗泵房內更換的藥水劑量設備、拆卸鄰近元朗泵房的舊渠務署人員宿舍、興建有照明的有蓋行人通道、在專線小巴、巴士、的士站興建行人侯車亭及改善青山公路旁的行人路和單車徑。</p>','2025-06-04 06:10:00.239000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.497000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.719000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',38.00),(591,'suibztehsuvis2h547sprmdc','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Design and Build Contract for Footbridge Linking Phase 8 Development','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Design and Build Contract for Footbridge Linking Phase 8 Development','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University','15 June 2015 - 29 August 2019','<p>The major scope of this project comprises the design and construction of a footbridge linking the Main Campus and the Phase 8 development of The Hong Kong Polytechnic University. The footbridge is designed as a steel bow-string arch structure with a main span length of 68m across the entire Chatham Road South. The pedestrian walkway with an overall width of about 7m and its associated sub-structures are hung from the two main arch beams by high-tensioned steel bar. The aesthetic form of the footbridge is designed according to the concept of &quot;Flying Fish&quot; and echoes with the surrounding iconic buildings of the University.</p><p>The works under the project include the design and construction of pile foundation, pile cap, RC lift shaft structures, lift installation, steel footbridge structure and its associated sub- structures, architectural works and finishes, building services works, footbridge connection works involving alternation and addition works to the existing Block Z at Phase 8 development.</p>','2025-06-03 02:52:56.166000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.543000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.752000',12,36,'en',8.00),(592,'maqwvacktll88dfxdxtq64go','香港國際機場貨運停機坪擴建工程','香港國際機場貨運停機坪擴建工程\n\n','香港機場管理局','2004 年 03 月 24 日 - 2005 年 05 月 31 日','<p>工程地點在高度敏感範圍，令進出地盤成為一個重大障礙。基於保安理由，每輛進出地盤的車輛都需要接受檢查及護送進出地盤。</p><br/><p>在機場跑道旁邊運送混凝土令施工上有很大的限制。因此特製了混凝土配料設備。此工程對鋪設路面的混凝土有嚴格的質量要求，需從德國進口，以達到高度品質的混凝土路面。</p>','2025-06-04 06:08:34.032000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.528000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.757000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',36.00),(593,'x1dyajodn599xidn19da5n2q','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works','Pillar Point Landfill Contract G - Sanitary Landfill and Associated Works','Civil Engineering Department','01 May 1996 - 30 September 1997','<p>The Works consisted of:</p>','2025-06-03 12:17:00.946000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.504000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.774000',3,36,'en',49.00),(594,'zv9xgpe7q4p79eba7gd93bzz','General Civil Works Contract No. HY/2014/18 Provision of Barrier-Free Access Facilities for Highways Structures - Phase 3 Contract 7','General Civil Works\nContract No. HY/2014/18 Provision of Barrier-Free Access Facilities for Highways Structures - Phase 3 Contract 7','Highways Department','25 November 2015 - 25 November 2019','<p>The Government has been installing barrier-free access facilities at public walkways and launched the “Universal Accessibility” (UA) Programme in August 2012 to proactively provide more barrier-free access facilities to facilitate public convenience in using public walkways.</p><br/><p>The works mainly comprise construction of 18 lifts, 6 ramps and 1 stairlift for 9 existing footbridges, 3 existing elevated walkways and 5 existing subways in 17 locations located in Eastern District, Wan Chai District, Southern District, Kowloon City District, Kwun Tong District, Yau Tsim Mong District and Kwai Tsing District; Associated with works above: civil works, geotechnical works, electrical and mechanical works, modification works for existing structures, roads and drainage works, landscaping works, etc. and Site investigation works as specified in the Contract.</p>','2025-06-03 02:41:52.193000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.591000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.796000',12,36,'en',6.00),(595,'cn3pggmqunqs7qa2q53ndivu','屯門公路改善工程 – 大欖段','屯門公路改善工程 – 大欖段\n\n','路政署','1998 年 09 月 01 日 - 2001 年 05 月 31 日','<p>屯門公路是連接屯門和九龍的主要道路。這項工程旨在為屯門公路大欖段現有的東行車道提供一條爬坡車道和硬路肩 ，並改善屯門公路上的斜坡。</p><p>本項目的其中一個重點為於屯門公路北側之岩石斜坡上進行開挖。為使開挖能安全地進行，不至影嚮斜坡下繁忙的交通，我司把公路南側隣近兄弟橋的山坡削平，建造臨時車道，把屯門公路東、西向的行車綫南移，遠離開挖進行的工地。同時，我司又調動施工的次序，先於分隔東西行車線的路中斜坡上，建造強化填料護土牆及新增的永久行車線，把東行的行車線南移，遠離北面的斜坡，騰出空間，於路旁建造臨時防滾石網及鋪設沙軟墊，以防止於斜坡開挖時鬆脫的石塊，滾下斜坡，對路過的車輛構成危險。</p><p>項目的另一重點為於分隔東西行車線的路中斜坡上設計及建造強化填料護土牆以興建一條新增的永久行車線。建造該段強化填料護土牆包括於斜坡上進行開挖。開挖期間，以臨時迷你樁牆枝撐東行車道的路基。建造護土牆的工序包括澆注鋼筋混凝土地基，於地基上按裝預制鋼筋混凝土構件，於構件背後分層回填、壓實及按裝特別填料及經熱浸鍍鋅處理的鋼制強化筋。為進行此部份之工程，我司特別設計及建造了一條鋼結構臨時橋，從青山公路旁的工地至位於分隔屯門公路東西行線的路中斜坡的工地，橫跨青山公路及屯門公路西行線，以便運送材料、機械、工具及人員行返工地。</p><p>在整個項目進行過程中，要碓保屯門公路東行之三條行車線暢通無阻。為進行重建現有的路面，我司設計及執行了一個極為複雜、多階段的逐行車線交通改道計劃。重建路面得以順利完成，並沒有對交通構成重大影嚮。</p>','2025-06-04 06:15:35.482000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.511000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.858000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',45.00),(596,'j0nyjfqecqwnzwsq35ch5gbv','Contract No. CV/2014/03 Provision of Universal Access Facilities for Highway Structures – Package 1 Contract 1','Contract No. CV/2014/03 Provision of Universal Access Facilities for Highway Structures – Package 1 Contract 1','Civil Engineering and Development Department','13 April 2015 - 12 April 2019','<p>The Government has been implementing measures to improve accessibility and usability of public facilities for all members of the community. In August 2012, the &quot;Universal Accessibility&quot; (UA) Programme was launched to proactively provide more barrier-free access facilities, such as ramps, lifts and tactile guide paths, in order to enhance the convenience and inclusivity of public walkways for users.</p><br/><p>This project consists of provision of 16 nos. of lifts in 8 locations, with 4 locations on the Hong Kong Island and 4 locations on the Kowloon Peninsula.</p>','2025-06-03 02:53:46.537000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.682000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.925000',12,36,'en',9.00),(597,'co7iiotfr7kkf2r210kc4tze','Contract No. HY/2013/12 Tuen Mun – Chek Lap Kok Link Northern Connection Toll Plaza and Associated Works','Contract No. HY/2013/12 Tuen Mun – Chek Lap Kok Link Northern Connection Toll Plaza and Associated Works','Highways Department','21 July 2014 - 21 September 2019','<p>The Tuen Mun–Chek Lap Kok Link (TM-CLKL) enhances connectivity between the New Territories, Lantau, the Hong Kong-Zhuhai-Macau Bridge (HZMB), and the airport. The new road reduces travel distance between the northwest and the airport by up to 22 km. The Northern connecting road section of TM-CLKL connecting road connects Tuen Mun Area 40 with the HZMB Hong Kong Port (HKP) via a sub-sea tunnel. The Southern connecting road section links the Hong Kong Port to North Lantau on via a series of viaducts.</p><br/><p>This project mainly comprises construction of the Northern connecting road section’s toll plaza covering an area of approximately 5.4 hectares and associated structures, carriageways and footbridge, as well as modification and realignment of sections of Lung Mun Road and Lung Fu Road at Tuen Mun, and associated works.</p>','2025-06-03 02:54:28.009000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.731000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.975000',12,36,'en',10.00),(598,'jqp0ehs8l8xntj9mzsen64a2','Hong Kong International Airport – Cargo Apron Extension Works','Hong Kong International Airport – Cargo Apron Extension Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','24 March 2004 - 31 May 2005','<p>Due to the highly sensitive nature of the area, access is a major obstacle. Construction vehicles have to be inspected and escorted every time they enter into the site for security reasons.</p><br/><p>The supply of fresh concrete into the site next to the airfield runway poses another major constraint. Special site concrete batching plants were constructed. The paving of the Pavement Quality Concrete requires a special automatic paver from Germany, the Wirtgen Slip form paver SP500 to achieve an extremely accurate quality finish of the concrete surface</p>','2025-06-03 12:04:25.269000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.931000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.180000',3,36,'en',36.00),(599,'ov5cdjd22c9f937f8eg3ba59','Midfield Parking Stands Upgrading Works','Midfield Parking Stands Upgrading Works ','Airport Authority Hong Kong','23 November 2006 - 05 August 2007','<p>The works consist of the Manufacture, Supply, Construction, Installation, Testing Commissioning and Design of the Midfield Parking Stands Upgrading Works</p><p>Site Clearance</p><p>Airfield Pavement Works</p><p>High Mast Lighting</p><p>System works</p><br/>','2025-06-03 04:05:10.424000','2025-07-07 07:27:39.966000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.255000',12,36,'en',27.00),(600,'r4r61n24066xouqwfs2yu5l5','Construction of Sewers, Rising Mains and Sewage Pumping Stations at Kam Tin, Nam Sang Wai and Au Tau in Yuen Long','Construction of Sewers, Rising Mains and Sewage Pumping Stations at Kam Tin, Nam Sang Wai and Au Tau in Yuen Long','Drainage Services Department','29 December 2005 - 30 June 2010','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><br/>','2025-06-03 04:06:56.026000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.113000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.335000',12,36,'en',29.00),(601,'ayhg2bgw2i8y8ita0xlwt7pt','Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan','Shatin New Town Stage II – Miscellaneous Civil Works in Sha Tin & Ma On Shan','Territory Development Department','26 March 2004 - 18 November 2006','<p>This project involved different types of civil works in Sha Tin and Ma On Shan with focus on slope, road and drainage works. Due to the inaccessibility of some work areas, special construction methods were employed. For the construction of the 120m long boulder fence at the remote hillside of To Shek Village, a helicopter delivered the boulder fence components to the site and the entire boulder fence was erected by manpower with a specially designed pulley system. While reinstating the 2km long existing seawall along the Ma On Shan promenade, both land and marine equipments were used to transport and place the rock armours. In view of the proximity of the existing seawall to the nearby residents, different environmental protective measures were exercised during the course of construction to avoid nuisance to the nearby public, while keeping the public well informed throughout the construction period.</p>','2025-06-03 12:03:37.077000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.109000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.324000',3,36,'en',35.00),(602,'fmh85l894b09okl5wuhuxed9','Shanxi Qilin Expressway','Shanxi Qilin Expressway','Shanxi Qilin Expressway Ltd','01 April 2001 - 30 November 2002','<p>Qilin expressway, which runs from the Qi county to the city of Lin Fen, is 177.72 km long and located in the middle south of the Shanxi Province. The width of road surface is 28.50 m and can accommodate 3 lanes of north and south bound traffic each way. Qilin expressway is part of the axial backbone of expressways in the providence. This backbone, measuring 666 km long, stretches from Da Tong to Yun Cheng, crossing the province from north to south. It is also the first expressway project in the province to be financed through the Asia Development Bank.</p><br/><p>The government of the province split the Qilin expressway project into 18 nos of contracts for subletting, and we were contract no. 16. This is a highway construction project of 14.3km in length and 28m in width of asphalt concrete pavement.</p><br/><p>The contract works commenced at the end of June 2001. During the course of construction, we managed the sub-contractors and our own resources to maintain working a minimum of 13 hours per day. The contract works were completed at the end of December 2002 and the project was appreciated by the client.</p>','2025-06-03 12:21:52.387000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.214000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.414000',3,36,'en',52.00),(603,'xk2q9bi7qss7qqen4bj9z3w8','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road – Tai Lam Section','Improvement to Tuen Mun Road – Tai Lam Section','Highways Department','01 September 1998 - 31 May 2001','<p>Tuen Mun Road is a highway linking Tuen Mun and Kowloon. This project is to provide a climbing lane and hard shoulder to the existing Eastbound Carriageway of Tuen Mun Road Tai Lam Section and will in addition improve the slopes above Tuen Mun Road.</p><br/><p>The major challenge of the project is the cutting back of the slope, in rock, above the live traffic of Tuen Mun Road at the slope toe. In order to proceed with the excavation safely, the South Rock Knob was excavated, temporarily diverting both the eastbound and westbound traffic away from the north slope. The reinforced fill retaining wall along the existing median was also constructed ahead of any works at the northern slopes so that an additional traffic lane was provided for the temporary diversion of the traffic away from the northern slope. A temporary roadside rock fall fence was then erected at the slope toe with sand cushion behind to catch any blocks of rock that become detached and fall down the slope during excavation.</p><br/><p>Another main feature of the project is the construction of the reinforced fill retaining wall at the Central Median for an extra traffic lane on top. This includes excavation at the existing slope of the Central median while temporarily supporting the existing eastbound carriageway (generally with pipe piles), erect precast concrete panels on the concrete footings and backfilling with selected fill materials sandwiched with galvanized steel reinforcing strips in layers. A temporary steel access bridge was constructed from the works area off Castle Peak Road, spanning across both the West bound carriageway of Tuen Mun Road and Castle Peak Road for the transportation of materials and plants to and from the site.</p><br/><p>Throughout the project, the 3-lane traffic along the eastbound carriageway of Tuen Mun Road has to be maintained at all times. A complicated traffic diversion scheme was adopted to maintain the traffic flow for the full depth carriageway reconstruction.</p>','2025-06-03 12:12:42.093000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.264000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.479000',3,36,'en',44.00),(604,'rdlyan08qpjqhv81le04132z','Uplifting Works to Promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area (Contract No. CV/2011/02)','Uplifting Works to Promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area (Contract No. CV/2011/02)','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 September 2011 - 31 December 2014','<p>This is a Design and Build project for the uplifting works to promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area. The objective of the works is to enhance the Aberdeen area and aim to further bring out the unique features of &#x27;traditional fishing harbour&#x27; and the local culture of Aberdeen and, by reinforcing the elements of diversified tourism, to enhance Aberdeen&#x27;s attractiveness to both international visitors and local residents.</p>','2025-06-03 03:00:40.779000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.265000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.571000',12,36,'en',17.00),(605,'nvhol5snmovdes6wxfo8bsze','Contract No. KL/2008/09 Kai Tak Development – Stage 1 Infrastructure Works at North Apron of Kai Tak Airport for Public Housing and Government Office Development','Contract No. KL/2008/09 Kai Tak Development – Stage 1 Infrastructure Works at North Apron of Kai Tak Airport for Public Housing and Government Office Development','Civil Engineering and Development Department','15 July 2009 - 23 August 2013','<p>The major scope of this project comprises the construction of approximately 2.6m long roads within the Project Site including the control, management, maintenance and diversion of existing roads, 2 footbridge FB1 and FB4, associated drainage including box culverts, sewerage and watermain works, enhancement and extension works of existing subways SW1, enhancement works of existing subways SW3 and SW5, landscape hardworks and softworks and environmental mitigation measures.</p><p>The works include realignment of Concorde Road, and construction of local Roads L2, L3, L4 (part) and L15. In conjunction with these roadworks are the associated street furniture, road markings and tra¬c signs, works for the highways structures (Footbridges, Subway, Enhancement Works) across Prince Edward Road East, construction of drainage, sewerage and fresh and salt water supplies systems to serve the Public Rental Housing (PRH) sites and the KTGO.</p><p>The works also include construction of two box culverts BC1 &amp; BC2, a 2.5m x 2.5m box culvert at Road L3 and its connection to the existing Nullah No. 2 and 3.0m x 2.8m box culvert along the amenity strip of Road L2 and its connection to the existing Kai Tak Nullah respectively, demolition of an existing ramp at the EMSD Headquarters ramp at the EMSD Headquarters crossing the Cargo Circuit, abandon the existing Nullah No. 1 and pipes, construction of 5 footpath connections from Road L2 to Subway SW5 and Wang Kong Road, improvement works at Kai Shing Street / Kai Wah Street junction, construction and installation of electrical and mechanical works for the infrastructure serving the early development at the North Apron area including the PRH sites and KTGO, landscape softworks and landscape hardworks.</p>','2025-06-03 03:54:02.466000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.391000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.617000',12,36,'en',23.00),(606,'g9onsff8pd56kx202ez8gzsh','Improvement to Pok Oi Interchange','Improvement to Pok Oi Interchange','Highways Department','30 November 2012 - 15 October 2016','<p>The Pok Oi Interchange Improvement Project is a NEC contract of Highways Department in November 2012 to ameliorate the Pok Oi Interchange by relieving traffic pressure on the existing interchange and meeting future traffic needs. The contract includes the construction of an additional flyover at Yuen Long Highway (towards Kowloon) at Pok Oi Interchange; the construction of a connecting slip road connecting the elevated road section and the ground section of Yuen Long Highway to Tuen Mun; building (near Pok Oi Hospital) a section of the left turn lane.</p><p>This project involves construction work in the centre and surrounding area of Pok Oi Interchange which is famous for its busy traffic. Traffic diversion restrictions, a narrow work space and complex public routes are some of the major challenges of this project.</p><p>In addition, this contract is special in that it adopts the NEC3 contract, emphasizing mutual trust and cooperation between contractors, project managers and property owners, promoting early settlement of engineering problems and locking up financial risks as early as possible. Through this contract, the project staff learnt more about the advantages of NEC3, its administrative requirements, working mode and contractual focus. It helped prepare the group for new trends in future government contracts.</p>','2025-06-03 02:58:49.337000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.332000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.687000',12,36,'en',16.00),(607,'w1cqzqr8f7bite57k6xaz93f','Civil Engineering and Development Department Contract No. CV/2013/08 Liantang / Heung Yuen Wai Boundary Control Point Site Formation and Infrastructure Works – Contract 6','Civil Engineering and Development Department Contract No. CV/2013/08 Liantang / Heung Yuen Wai Boundary Control Point Site Formation and Infrastructure Works – Contract 6','Civil Engineering and Development Department','24 June 2015 - 21 June 2019','<p>The LT/HYW BCP is the seventh land-based BCP between Hong Kong and Shenzhen. At present, there are two land-based BCPs at Man Kam To and Sha Tau Kok. Owing to geographical constraints, however, these two BCPs have little room for further expansion. Situated between Man Kam To and Sha Tau Kok, the LT/HYW BCP will make up for the inadequacies and make cross-boundary transportation and connections between Hong Kong and the eastern part of Guangdong Province as well as the Fujian and Jiangxi Provinces more convenient and efficient. This can help expand Hong Kong&#x27;s economic hinterland.</p><br/><p>It comprises the construction of an approximately 4.6km long dual two-lane Connecting Road connecting the BCP with the proposed Sha Tau Kok Interchange and the associated tunnel ventilation buildings. Provision of sewage collection, treatment and disposal facilities for the BCP and the resite of Chuk Yuen Village and the associated environmental mitigation measures, and Environmental Monitoring and Audit (EM&amp;A)</p>','2025-06-03 02:52:08.606000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.545000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.771000',12,36,'en',7.00),(608,'wa4topbui3oglezdbprlds22','Retrofitting of Noise Barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridge at Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches','Retrofitting of Noise Barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridge at Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches','Highways Department','08 January 2008 - 09 July 2011','<p>The major elements of Works consisted of:</p>','2025-06-03 03:55:30.237000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.669000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.884000',12,36,'en',24.00),(609,'n4146sjby637sfmo49fks6ai','Village Flood Protection Works for San Tin Villages','Village Flood Protection Works for San Tin Villages','Drainage Project Division','20 November 1996 - 26 December 2000','<p>The pumping station on raft foundation and its associated storage pond were the major construction works on site. A total of 1,740m long x 3.5m wide, embankment/access road had to be built for flood protection purposes.</p><br/><p>The floodwater flows into the chambers &amp; the pipes system and then to the storage pond. The 5-trough pumping station would begin operating when the floodwater comes up to a certain level upon which the floodwater would pass through a twin-cell box culvert and flow downstream.</p><br/><p>A series of water diversions were required to maintain the stream flow from the San Tin Villages out to the Shen Zhen River.</p><br/><p>For the slope embankment, precast concrete grasscrete blocks are the final surface above the layer of the concrete lining, granular fill &amp; general fill. The grasscrete blocks were designed with open area for hydroseeding and they have to be reinforced together in order to avoid the tidal effect of the floodwater.</p><br/><p>The major difficulties involved in the project were the ground water flow from the adjacent fish ponds and the limited working area along the embankment. Temporary cofferdams formed with sheet piles had to installed in order to cut off the underground water for construction purpose.</p>','2025-06-03 12:15:30.807000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.742000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.947000',3,36,'en',47.00),(610,'ejcmug1xmmetnd2cgqp42w4b','大埔發展項目第12及39區場地平整工程','大埔發展項目第12及39區場地平整工程\n\n','拓展署','1998 年 03 月 18 日 - 2003 年 05 月 05 日','<p>建造長1.6公里的主幹道和長7.3公里直徑600釐米的水管及相關工程。這些工程包括：</p>','2025-06-04 06:16:28.452000','2025-07-07 07:27:40.727000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.050000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',46.00),(611,'t5n3jwsr4b4t23kwhw3ku5a8','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1111 Hung Hom North Approach Tunnels','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1111 Hung Hom North Approach Tunnels','MTR Corporation Limited','17 December 2012 - 18 November 2018','<p>The Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a government funded concessionary project providing a strategic rail corridor from Shatin to Central. One of the contracts of the Shatin to Central Link (SCL). The scope of work is included Tunnels Works, Foundation Works, Site Formation Works, Bridge Works, Noise Enclosure Works and Demolition Works. This is a challenging project in terms of geographical location and work complexity, as this construction site will pass through the aged urban town Hung Hom where a huge amount of utilities are underground. Due to the location, extensive TTM arrangements and utilities diversion and/or protection has to be undertaken.</p>','2025-06-03 02:57: