i Yuen Estate and Fanling Centre','Noise Barriers on Fanling Highway near Choi Yuen Estate and Fanling Centre','Highways Department','23 August 2004 - 20 March 2006','<p>The major works of this project is to construct approx. 600m long vertical noise barriers and approx. 2400m long cantilever noise barriers along Fanling Highway.</p>','2025-06-03 12:01:04.651000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.195000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.401000',3,36,'en',32.00),(616,'k9629pbm7fkxobaaja3ty3kr','Lantau and Airport Railway Siu Ho Wan Depot, Phase I','Lantau and Airport Railway Siu Ho Wan Depot, Phase I','Mass Transit Railway Corporation','01 January 1995 - 31 May 1998','<p>This was one of the projects of the Airport Core Programme therefore timely completion of the works was critical. The main depot building completion was paramount for the success of the project.</p><br/><p>As there was no land access to the site for this multi-discipline project, careful consideration had to be given to procurement, delivery, and storage of materials.</p><br/><p>The completion of the North Lantau Expressway bridge and associated access roads and embankments within a 3 month period exemplified the project team&#x27;s teamwork &amp; determination to complete the works on time.</p>','2025-06-03 12:18:18.241000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.073000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.413000',3,36,'en',51.00),(617,'ayodlar9yg42icmd51xqbfjq',' Kai Tak Development - Stage 3A Infrastructure at Former North Apron Area (Contract No. KL/2012/02)','\nKai Tak Development - Stage 3A Infrastructure at Former North Apron Area ','Civil Engineering and Development Department','15 July 2013 - 27 April 2017','<p>The major works of this contract included construction of new roads about 890 metres (m) in total length covering L1, Road L11 and a slip road linking Prince Edward Road East (PERE) to Road D1, a vehicular underpass about 225m long across part of Prince Edward Road East , a new pedestrian subway of about 205m long, and extension of an existing subway about 60m in total length, across PERE, modification and widening of existing roads in former Kai Tak Airport north apron area and San Po Kong area, construction of associated footpaths, street lighting, traffic aids, drainage, sewerage, water mains, landscaping works and electrical and mechanical works, and provision of necessary environmental mitigation measures and implementation of an environmental monitoring and audit programme associated with the above works.</p>','2025-06-03 02:55:38.044000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.166000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.459000',12,36,'en',11.00),(618,'eqqaybowkaaltd07j8shusj3','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I','Tai Po Development Formation and Servicing of Area 12 (Part) and 39 – Phase I','Territory Development Department','18 March 1998 - 05 May 2003','<p>Construction of 1.6km long trunk road together with 7.3km of water main of size up to 600mm diameter and associated works. These works included: a 450m long rectangular box culvert and a sea outfall; 4 nos. 6m high retaining wall; installation of 234m pavement soil nail and import of 300,000m³ filling material.</p>','2025-06-03 12:13:35.923000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.261000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.491000',3,36,'en',45.00),(619,'gmblzn9wzynsqwari4esul7j','土木及基礎工程','土木及基礎工程\n\n','九廣鐵路','1999 年 07 月 02 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>該合約包括西鐵車廠及錦田站的建造，安裝，土木及基建的設計。該工程包括所有地盤平整，渠務，道路，公用設施，環境美化，主要排水渠道及軌道路基平整工程。</p><p>這些道路工程包括興建一條約660米長的雙程高架橋橫跨地盤，消防和公共通道，停車場及道路交匯處設施。</p>','2025-06-04 06:14:11.412000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.359000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.632000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',43.00),(620,'nhy2f73z4ayufp3wdyhepwib','美孚站','美孚站\n\n','九廣鐵路公司','1999 年 08 月 02 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>美孚站位於荔枝角公園內，採用密封式設計。其設計特色在於使車站與公園環境融爲一體。車站的天台更被設計成爲空中花園。其中包括園林綠化及各種休憩設施。爲鄰近的大型高密度住宅屋村如美孚新村及清麗苑等的居民提供服務。本站的整體設計及建造，均以融合鄰近的民居及環境爲主題。例如：提供充足的行人及行車通道從車站接駁到鄰近的屋苑等。於建築期間，減低對居民的影響，也是一個重要的議題。所以，在建築期間，特別建造了一條臨時行人天橋橫跨整個工地，爲居民提供方便的來往通道。由於西鐵的通車，美孚站及其天台上的空中花園落成啓用，鄰近一帶地區的交通及環境得以大幅改善，居民的生活質素也相應提高。</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-04 06:13:34.857000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.474000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.664000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',42.00),(621,'agmd82y87h8obne1i5kridlq','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','11 April 1997 - 26 March 1999','<br/>','2025-06-03 12:14:41.982000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.484000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.696000',3,36,'en',46.00),(622,'vuqlfblvjh81auif0rdrl9u6','屯門 38區特別工業區發展 – 填海、海堤、道路、水道','屯門 38區特別工業區發展 – 填海、海堤、道路、水道\n\n','土木工程拓展署','1995 年 09 月 01 日 - 2000 年 01 月 31 日','<p>這項工程包括建造450m長垂直海牆、1000m 長碎石斜坡海牆、建造625m長4 組排水暗渠與道路、污水道、排水道、食水管道和填海28公頃。</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-04 06:20:51.727000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.552000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.896000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',51.00),(623,'l769y69ukmxgfonaptttwp44','Contract No. NE/2015/02 Tseung Kwan O - Lam Tin Tunnel, Road P2 and Associated Works','Contract No. NE/2015/02 Tseung Kwan O - Lam Tin Tunnel, Road P2 and Associated Works','Civil Engineering and Development Department','29 July 2016 - 28 September 2023','<p>The Tseung Kwan O - Lam Tin Tunnel (TKO-LTT) is intended to address growing external traffic demands from Tseung Kwan O&#x27;s ongoing development. Together with the proposed Trunk Road T2 and Central Kowloon Route, the TKO-LTT will form the express Route 6 network linking West Kowloon and Tseung Kwan O.</p><br/><p>This project is part of the TKO-LTT which includes constructing an 800m dual two-lane highway (Road P2), with around 600m in the form of a depressed carriageway, 200m of which will be covered by a landscape deck. Associated building, civil, structural, marine, electrical, mechanical, landscaping, environmental protection, and mitigation works are also included.</p>','2025-06-03 02:41:00.342000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.729000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.938000',12,36,'en',5.00),(624,'nuwq9b4x07djtiowyb0jo4xf','Sha Tin New Town, Stage II Road T6 and Interchanges','Sha Tin New Town, Stage II Road T6 and Interchanges','Territory Development Department','01 June 1988 - 31 October 1991','<p>Over a thousand tonnes of fabricated steel false work was required for the high level bridge.</p><br/><p>Pile Caps for the marine bridge piers were constructed in precast concrete permanent shells which were lowered into position on the bored piles using strand jacks before making watertight seals and concreting.</p><br/><p>Temporary piles were installed to support the false work for the reinforced concrete V-shaped piers.</p><br/><p>Over 300 large diameter bored piles were constructed by the company.</p>','2025-06-03 12:24:45.148000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.781000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.027000',3,36,'en',55.00),(625,'zfapn8d1a3zdc6ww3f1w1ru5','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun','River Trade Terminal Area 38, Tuen Mun','River Trade Terminal Co. Ltd','01 November 1996 - 30 November 1999','<p>This project involved large-scale marine engineering works to create a 65-hectare site for the River Trade Terminal in Hong Kong. The experience gained on other major marine projects over the years allowed our company to handle the enormous scope of work required to complete the project within a very tight programme; the first phase of the project was completed a month ahead of schedule. Among our many responsibilities under this contract, which was awarded by a private consortium of some of Hong Kong’s leading companies, was dredging over 3 million cubic metres of marine mud, constructing two 2.1-km long, 1.6-metre in diameter and one 730-metre long 2.1-metre diameter submarine pipelines, building 3.3 km of vertical seawalls, constructing a 530 metre breakwater and extensive ground improvement works. Importation of 11million cubic metres of sandfill was a critical activity of the programme; delivery rates of up to 60,000 cubic metres of sand per day were achieved from our sources in the PRC. Manufacture and installation of over 37,000 seawall blocks was another key activity. To ensure control of the production we manufactured all of the blocks at Wai Kee’s own precasting yard at Niu Tau Island in the PRC. A crucial element of this contract was the careful co-ordination of the follow-on civil engineering and building works.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 12:16:11.194000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.819000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.043000',3,36,'en',48.00),(626,'n9edx8nqfbeb5mjunndfmqmc','Contract No. HY/2008/12 Bus-Bus Interchanges on Tuen Mun Road','Contract No. HY/2008/12 Bus-Bus Interchanges on Tuen Mun Road','Highways Department','15 July 2010 - 31 July 2015','<p>The works mainly comprise the construction of a bus-bus interchange on Tuen Mun Road Kowloon-bound near Siu Lam Interchange and Tai Lam Kok roundabout, the widening of Brothers&#x27; Bridge, and the construction of a link bridge with two lifts. It will allow passengers to travel on foot from the holding area at TMR to the holding area at Tai Lam Kok to switch buses. Two lifts will be constructed in connection with the link bridge to provide access to people with disabilities. Its associated civil works include road reconstruction, provision of shelters, drainage, landscaping, traffic aids and street lighting, slope works, waterworks, and provisioning of works for traffic control surveillance.</p><p>The project aims at providing a convenient interchange facility for passengers to switch amongst bus routes from/to Northwest New Territories operating via Tuen Mun Road. This arrangement will not only provide passengers more choices of bus services at the bus-bus interchange, but also greatly enhance the overall efficiency of the bus network in the Northwest New Territories and reduce traffic congestion and road-side air pollution.</p>','2025-06-03 03:51:13.666000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.833000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.160000',12,36,'en',20.00),(627,'vv8qaq91j048v89numuhsit5','Tuen Mun Area 38 Special Industries Area Development – Reclamation, Seawall, Road & Drains','Tuen Mun Area 38 Special Industries Area Development – Reclamation, Seawall, Road & Drains','Port Works Division / Civil Engineering Department','01 September 1995 - 31 January 2000','<p>This project includes the construction of 450m long vertical seawall, 1000m long sloping rubble seawall, 625m long 4-cells drainage culvert, roads, sewers, drains and watermains and reclamation of 28 hectares of land.</p>','2025-06-03 12:17:38.834000','2025-07-07 07:27:41.983000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.211000',3,36,'en',50.00),(628,'jiy1yyxd600dxa9krcknbac1','屯門道路改善工程','屯門道路改善工程\n\n','路政署','1994 年 05 月 01 日 - 1996 年 09 月 30 日','<p>該項目主要包括設計及建造屯門公路四個關鍵性的上坡路段（汀九，大欖，掃管笏及三聖墟）的路線工程，總長度為8.5公里; 在31個削土斜坡和17個填土斜坡上進行岩土穩固工程; 6個擋土牆; 六座橋樑，五條地下通道及深井行人天橋結構加固工程。</p><br/><p>我們在施工過程中執行有限度的交通改道措施以減少建造時對大眾之幹擾。</p>','2025-06-04 06:23:24.115000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.009000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.226000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',54.00),(629,'fbrjrm6guy7bbgtfd7ne6e5x','Sky City Car Park and Utility Works','Sky City Car Park and Utility Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','31 May 2005 - 20 December 2005','<p>Our company is the first to apply the GFA pavement in Hong Kong. GFA is the acronym for granular materials treated with ‘fly ash’ or PFA. GFA is a slow setting, slow hardening mixture which has the benefit of an unbound material in the short-term allowing longer handling time, and as a bound material in the medium to long term provides equivalent if not better structural characteristics of conventional bound materials such as bituminous base course.</p><br/><p>GFA utilizes PFA, a by-product waste from coal-fired energy generation, making it a more economical and environmentally friendly pavement alternative.</p>','2025-06-03 12:00:21.458000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.036000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.247000',3,36,'en',31.00),(630,'he6l4w1kcb40hdavc4rckw78','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No.1106 Diamond Hill Station','Shatin to Central Link – Contract No.1106 Diamond Hill Station','MTR Corporation Limited','17 December 2012 - 18 November 2018','<p>The 17-kilometre SCL was a territory-wide strategic railway project involving 10 stations, amongst which Diamond Hill was one of the six interchange stations. Upon the completion of Diamond Hill Station, it will become a new interchange station for the future SCL and the existing Kwun Tong Line.</p><p>The scope of SCL1106 included construction of a new SCL concourse and platforms and a wide array of enhanced facilities including the installation of 3 new lifts, 12 escalators, additional ticket issuing machines, automatic teller machines, shops, and new public toilet facilities. The scope also includes the relocation of heritage structures and archaeological diggings.</p>','2025-06-03 02:58:11.282000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.037000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.241000',12,36,'en',15.00),(631,'fig8pc62rlzt4atbvdzoqu9v','Interchange at Pok Fu Lam Road and Sassoon Road','Interchange at Pok Fu Lam Road and Sassoon Road','Highways Department','16 December 1998 - 31 March 2003','<p>Widening of the section of Pok Fu Lam Road fronting Queen Mary Hospital involving the construction of new carriageway (partly on elevated structures) and reconstruction of existing carriageway; re-alignment of the upper section of Sassoon Road at its junction with Pok Fu Lam Road involving the replacement of the existing carriageway with new carriageway (partly on elevated structures); construction of a link bridge linking the re-aligned Sassoon Road and the access road to Queen Mary Hospital; re-alignment of the upper section of Bisney Road at its junction with Pok Fu Lam Road involving the replacement of existing carriageway with new carriageway (partly on elevated structures); demolition of the existing footbridge across Pok Fu Lam Road and construction of a new footbridge at the same location; and associated drainage, landscaping, retaining walls and slope works.</p>','2025-06-03 12:11:29.180000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.059000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.298000',3,36,'en',43.00),(632,'v8vs541jbcwlu1dejy5nzffg','Business Aviation Centre Expansion Works','Business Aviation Centre Expansion Works ','Airport Authority Hong Kong','16 November 2007 - 25 January 2009','<p>The works include an extension of existing Taxi lane Z3 and additional parking stands with BAC Expansion.</p>','2025-06-03 03:56:37.931000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.412000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.640000',12,36,'en',25.00),(633,'uaikljo85g4lkxlztz3z53r2','Shatin to Central Link Contract No. 1108 Kai Tak Station and Associated Tunnels','Shatin to Central Link Contract No. 1108 Kai Tak Station and Associated Tunnels','MTR Corporation Limited','25 April 2013 - 18 November 2018','<p>The Shatin to Central Link (SCL) is a government funded concessionary project providing a strategic rail corridor from Shatin to Central. One of the contracts of the Shatin to Central Link (SCL), the works comprise the construction of the Kai Tak Station and associate tunnels.</p><p>Consisting of 2 levels of RC box structure constructed by cut and cover method, this underground station is located in centre of Kai Tak Development Area. Upon completion of the project, Kai Tak residents will benefit as crossing the harbour will take much less time.</p>','2025-06-03 02:56:19.772000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.334000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.676000',12,36,'en',12.00),(634,'f99yheowd38vi9qf0j1luhns','沙田新市鎮城第II 階工程－T6 號道路及交匯處工程','沙田新市鎮城第II 階工程－T6 號道路及交匯處工程\n\n','拓展署','1988 年 06 月 01 日 - 1991 年 10 月 31 日','<p>此橋梁使用逾千噸之裝配式鋼管工作架。</p><br/><p>河中橋墩之樁帽採用預鑄模式施工法，在基樁施作不透水封及混凝土灌漿前，即將預鑄模以千斤頂固定於樁內。</p><br/><p>雙V型橋墩施工期間，須加打臨時樁以支撐工作架。</p><br/><p>現場灌築逾三百支大口徑螺旋樁。</p><br/><br/><p>雙V型橋墩施工期間，須加打臨時樁以支撐工作架。</p><br/><br/><p>現場灌築逾三百支大口徑螺旋樁。</p>','2025-06-04 06:24:04.720000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.470000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.710000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',55.00),(635,'jurgzxg7n08ks5dykib76o49','Airfield Stop Bar Relocation Works','Airfield Stop Bar Relocation Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','19 July 2005 - 09 April 2006','<p>The entire installation works is carried out at night to minimize disturbance to the airfields. Daily detail works plans are carefully planed and perfectly orchestrated at night to maximize productivity under the tight working hours. Although the physical airfield works are only carried out at night, the project requires a 24-hours-a-day input from the project team.</p><br/><p>Pre-cast concrete bases (constructed on site during the day) are perfect for a quick installation of the stop bar light system.</p><br/><p>The transformer housings units of the airfield ground lighting system are imported directly from the United States to meet the stringent requirements for airfields usages.</p>','2025-06-03 11:56:45.111000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.409000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.736000',3,36,'en',30.00),(636,'unsqf33mn47zfq2s87mtexsg','屯門38區內河貨櫃碼頭','屯門38區內河貨櫃碼頭\n\n','內河碼頭有限公司','1996 年 11 月 01 日 - 1999 年 11 月 30 日','<p>主要工程包括：</p><br/>','2025-06-04 06:19:01.629000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.607000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.840000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',49.00),(637,'yzydw6xid1v8u0vrtlk45wh3','Public Transport Interchange at Long Ping Station','Public Transport Interchange at Long Ping Station','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','23 September 2002 - 11 October 2003','<p>The Construction of Public Transport Interchanges at Long Ping Station on two sites serves the new West Rail works and includes other works to tie in with works already being constructed under other West Rail Contracts. Our group was awarded this project, which includes the construction of an uncovered Public Transport Interchange at the south of the Long Ping Station for green minibuses and taxis, the works comprise all civil, architectural, landscape and building services works including earthworks, retaining walls, roadworks, footways, drainage works, utility diversions, fencing, finishes and other related works. The PTI at the north of the Long Ping Station is uncovered, catering for franchised bus, residential coaches, taxis and private vehicles. The works consisted of all civil, architectural, landscape and building services works including earthworks, roadworks, drainage works, utility diversions, fencing, finishes and other related works. Other works include the foundation and superstructure works for the staircase, lift-shaft, escalator trough and bridge section to connect to the new section constructed by others, demolition of the existing DSD Staff quarters adjacent to the Yuen Long Pumping Station down to ground level.</p>','2025-06-03 12:05:59.977000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.568000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.817000',3,36,'en',38.00),(638,'zdvkc5a8zpjxv6e8knzutm0h','Contract No. HY/2019/02 Lift and Pedestrian Walkway System between Castle Peak Road and Kung Yip Street, Kwai Chung','Contract No. HY/2019/02 Lift and Pedestrian Walkway System between Castle Peak Road and Kung Yip Street, Kwai Chung','Highways Department','19 December 2019 - 31 December 2023','<p>To construct a pedestrian infrastructure that is convenient, safe, environmentally friendly, and barrier-free, will enhance convenience and accessible pedestrian traffic for local residents, including the elderly and disabled, between the Shek Lei area, Castle Peak Road – Kwai Chung, and Kung Yip Street.</p><br/><p>The project includes construction of a lift and pedestrian walkway system connecting Shek Lei area, Castle Peak Road – Kwai Chung and Kung Yip Street, with 3 lift towers, 2 covered, elevated pedestrian walkways and 2 staircases.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 02:26:22.427000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.686000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.904000',12,36,'en',1.00),(639,'blijm6c8d7499tqwcqf6e59l','Contract No. HY/2016/04 Elevated Walkway between Tong Ming Street and Tong Tak Street , Tseung Kwan O','Contract No. HY/2016/04 Elevated Walkway between Tong Ming Street and Tong Tak Street , Tseung Kwan O','Highways Department','30 December 2016 - 03 March 2021','<p>The main purpose of this project is to construct an elevated walkway connecting the existing footbridge across Tong Ming Street to the shopping mall above Tseung Kwan O MTR Station and a lift at the end of the elevated walkway near Tong Tak Street to provide a comfortable and convenient access for residents (especially the elderly) of Tseung Kwan O town centre. The existing cycle parking area at Tong Ming Street is to be reconstructed and expanded to increase the number of cycle parking spaces for use by the residents of the area.</p><br/><p>This contract mainly comprises construction of an elevated walkway of about 180 m in length and about 5 m in clear width, connecting the existing footbridge across Tong Ming Street to the shopping mall above Tseung Kwan O MTR Station; construction of a lift at the end of the proposed elevated walkway near Tong Tak Street; reconstruction and expansion of the existing cycle parking area; and ancillary works, including associated road, drainage, public utilities, public lighting, landscaping, and electrical and mechanical works.</p>','2025-06-03 02:39:46.697000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.745000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.927000',12,36,'en',3.00),(640,'a2xe5s15eoba1g0sqg5rhyqw','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road','Highways Department','10 June 2004 - 29 May 2008','<p>One of the most complex and challenging aspects of this project is the temporary traffic arrangements (TTA) while constructing the flyover in the highly congested area of Causeway Bay.</p><br/><p>Numerous traffic simulations analyses are required to study the impact of each TTA scenario. The analyses requires tremendous amount of data to accurately predict the effects of any chosen TTA.</p><br/><p>A 70m long temporary steel off ramp was constructed to maintain the existing traffic flow, with part of the existing flyover initially demolished to allow the construction of the proposed flyover.</p><br/><p>The low soffit level of the proposed flyover with gradients in both directions and the road height clearance requirement coupled with the excessively long span over Victoria Park Road made the design of the falsework decking nearly impossible. The depth of the deck had to meet the various road height clearances, and structural requirements.</p>','2025-06-03 12:02:52.306000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.764000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.957000',3,36,'en',34.00),(641,'pdpsllzvwd41spv65jjy7cyh','新田農村防洪工程','新田農村防洪工程\n\n','渠務署','1996 年 11 月 20 日 - 2000 年 12 月 26 日','<p>乘托於筏式基礎上的泵房及其相關的洪水儲水池塘爲本專案之重點工程。本專案也包括建造圍繞新田村，長約1.74公里之圍堤及於圍堤上建造之1.35米闊的行車通道。</p><br/><p>新田村一帶地區的洪水會流經一系列之沙井及溝渠，進入與泵房相連的儲水池塘。當塘內洪水的水位升至預設之水位時，泵房的5漕抽水系統便會啟動，把洪水經由雙孔箱形暗渠輸送到深圳河的下游。</p><br/><p>爲確保流經新田村至深圳河的溪流不受影向，工程期間進行了一系列的臨時溪流改道。</p><br/><p>圍堤的設計從內至外爲：一般填土、碎石層、混凝土襯層。最後在斜坡面鋪設預製混凝土草磚。草磚有特別開孔設計以供噴草。個別草磚之間也互相扣緊，承受洪水漲退的影響。</p><br/><p>本專案之主要困難爲在建造泵房基礎時，處理從鄰近的漁塘流進的地下水。同時，用於建造圍堤的非常有限的工作空間，也爲施工隊伍帶來很大的挑戰。施工隊以鋼板樁建造臨時圍堰，以有效地控制流進基礎範圍的地下水。</p>','2025-06-04 06:18:02.792000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.699000','2025-07-07 07:27:42.973000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',48.00),(642,'w25hs3id2t9fwb6g17dm0vic','Sha Tin New Town, Stage II Route5 - Sha Tin Connection, Phase I','Sha Tin New Town, Stage II Route5 - Sha Tin Connection, Phase I','Territory Development Department','01 June 1987 - 31 October 1991','<p>This project involves the construction of the Shatin approach to the Shing Mun Tunnels, and is part of the Route 5 Expressway linking Shatin and Tsuen Wan. The 2km long expressway begins at Tai Po Road near the KCR Shatin Station and rises on a 13 span elevated viaduct over the railway line and Tai Po Road to an abutment halfway along the route to the tunnel portals.</p><br/><p>Along the 1 km expressway near Mei Lam Estate, 1-2m high transparent noise barriers were built to minimize noise disturbance to the local residents.</p><br/><p>There was a high degree of complexity in the construction of cross heads of various sizes. Two main types of false work were specially designed and used in the project.</p><br/><p>A total of 486 precast post-tensioned concrete U-beams were manufactured on site with lifting gantries and transportation equipment designed in house. A wide range of beam lengths added to the complexity. Special gantries were purposefully designed and built by the company for lifting and placing precast beams weighing 65 tonnes.</p>','2025-06-03 12:25:43.571000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.100000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.322000',3,36,'en',56.00),(643,'fsgq1uh3dijs6x0dx0kfe9ik','東涌發展第一期基建工程','東涌發展第一期基建工程\n\n','拓展署','1994 年 07 月 01 日 - 1997 年 01 月 31 日','<p>此預應力混凝土橋支撐架構爲六座海上橋墩及兩端陸上橋座組成。每處橋座以十二支直徑達一米半及長達五十六米之陸上螺旋樁爲支撐，而每座海上橋墩以十二支直徑達一米半之海上樁爲支撐。</p><br/><p>海底基樁以駁船載運每節24-30米長之套管樁至定位鑽掘接合而成。</p>','2025-06-04 06:22:41.579000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.084000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.355000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',53.00),(644,'mpvcpilpz5xmweo2cej0nasq','薄扶林道及沙孫道交通交匯處','薄扶林道及沙孫道交通交匯處\n\n','路政署','1998 年 12 月 16 日 - 2003 年 03 月 31 日','<p>本專案的重點爲擴闊一段在全港規模最大，最主要的瑪麗醫院前的薄扶林道與及改善其鄰近的路口，提供一個暢通無阻的交匯處。確保緊急車輛能夠儘快進出醫院，也改善附近一帶地區的交通流量。在擴闊薄扶林道的部份，工程包括在陡峭的斜坡上建造一段高架行車道。同時，也包括把現有的薄扶林道拉直及重建。並重建沙孫道及薄扶林道路口。此外，本專案也包括以重建的沙孫道爲起點，建造一條連接瑪麗醫院的連接橋。重建班士尼道與薄扶林道路口。其部份路面也是於斜坡上興建的高架行車道。由於大部份的高架行車道的結構工程都是在陡峭的斜坡上進行，工程的難度大大的提高。尤其是在進行基礎工程的階段。爲建造現澆攪拌樁承建商採用了大規模的臨時工作臺及在斜坡上開挖的臨時平臺。薄扶林道爲連接港島西區及南區的其中一條主要通道，交通流量非常高，車速又快。於工程進行期間，爲確保交通安全及暢順，承建商提供了大量的相關操施，包括：建造臨時擴闊路面，提供及安裝大量的交通標置，指示及照明系統等。</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-04 06:14:50.490000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.106000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.433000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',44.00),(645,'pn9l7ahexsma9a6y9dc5umtt','Development of EcoPark in Tuen Mun Area 38','Development of EcoPark in Tuen Mun Area 38','Environmental Protection Department','03 July 2006 - 01 January 2010','<p>The EcoPark is a key element of the strategy that aims to promote the local recycling industry and jump-start a sustainable economy by providing long-term land facility for the environmental and recycling industry. By encouraging and promoting the reuse, recovery and recycling of our waste resources and return them to the consumption loop, the EcoPark will help capitalize the potential of the local recycling industry and alleviate the heavy demand of the Hong Kong landfills.</p><br/><p>EcoPark occupies 20 hectares of land in Tuen Mun Area 38 and will be developed in two phases. Phase I of EcoPark (about 8 ha) will be available for occupation towards the end of 2006 and Phase II (about 12 ha) in 2009. Various environmentally friendly features are being used for the first time in Hong Kong, such as the Sun Pipe, Solar power water faucet, and a Green roof just to name a few.</p>','2025-06-03 04:05:54.799000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.228000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.465000',12,36,'en',28.00),(646,'nhpowaq1af6fatl75zbmigh9','九龍觀塘康寧道公園第一期建造工程','九龍觀塘康寧道公園第一期建造工程\n\n','建築署','1997 年 04 月 11 日 - 1999 年 03 月 26 日','<br/>','2025-06-04 06:17:22.929000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.362000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.559000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',47.00),(647,'trtelmv3jf7eopd1kd708j4a','Mei Foo Station','Mei Foo Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved. The quality of living for the local residents was also enhanced.</p>','2025-06-03 12:09:59.156000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.244000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.553000',3,36,'en',41.00),(648,'pzft8rqymanm36y0lpihca16','Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central-Wan Chai Bypass at Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre (Contract No: HK/2009/01)','Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central-Wan Chai Bypass at Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre ','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 December 2009 - 31 May 2016','<p>The key purpose of Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.</p><p>The group was awarded one of the contracts in Wan Chai Development Phase II, the works mainly include land formation and construction of the Central-Wan Chai Bypass (CWB) tunnel at the water channel between the two phases of Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre (HKCEC) and other associated works.</p>','2025-06-03 03:52:32.265000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.312000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.567000',12,36,'en',21.00),(649,'fbr6g3wkerzhm2od6xj419pb','Nam Cheong Station','Nam Cheong Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','01 October 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Nam Cheong Station is the southern terminal of the West Rail. It is an interchange station for the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The structure envelopes the alignments of the existing elevated West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the existing Airport Express Line (AEL) and the MTR Tung Chung Line. It also includes the linking carriageway and the associated elevated flyover system. During the construction stage, the West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line have to maintain normal operations. These requirements greatly increased the difficulties in the construction and required extremely high and stringent construction techniques.</p><br/><p>This station includes the track side platforms at ground level and an underground station hall for both the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The underground station hall was constructed underneath the operating Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line. In order to ensure the operation of the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line, “Top down” construction method was employed. This kind of construction method on such a scale is seldom seen in Hong Kong.The underground station hall and platform design ensured the utilization and development of the underground space, and reduce occupied area at ground level. It also provided a grand outlook of the station. Apart from providing business activities, with the highly efficient pedestrian flow design, the crowds are quickly diverted to the relevant Airport Express Line station, bus station, residential blocks and commercial areas.</p><br/><p>The column, beam structure and foundation design of the station have made provisions for the future development of multi-storey residential blocks on top of the station. The foundations design includes large diameter cast in-situ concrete bored piles, diaphragm walls and driven steel H-piles, etc. Reinforced concrete column structures were reserved at the roof slab of the station for future construction of the multi-storey resident blocks. The multi-storey shear walls of the future superstructures will be supported by the transfer plate at the station roof. This accommodates any future change in the layout of the superstructure.</p>','2025-06-03 12:09:13.933000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.403000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.622000',3,36,'en',40.00),(650,'l4cwxp7wlul1k4fjl7ba6c9o','Tseung Kwan O Further Development – Design and Build of Infrastructure Works for Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill Site (Phase I)','Tseung Kwan O Further Development – Design and Build of Infrastructure Works for Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill Site (Phase I) ','Highways Department','29 December 2009 - 03 April 2012','<p>The Tseung Kwan O Further Development is to improve the overall design of the town with the vision to build Tseung Kwan O into a new town that can boast of its convenience, unique urban design of quality living environment.</p><p>This is one of the Tseung Kwan O Further Development projects, which mainly improves the linkage between Tseung Kwan O Stage 1 landfill site and the adjacent areas for supporting the future recreational developments at the landfill site. It includes the construction of a 2.0km footpath and 1.6km cycle track connecting Tseung Kwan O Stage I Landfill site and Tseung Kwan O Town Centre South; construction of an approximate 140m long bridge for pedestrians and cyclists; construction of about 1 km of grasscrete paved access and landscape works.</p>','2025-06-03 03:53:20.894000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.426000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.698000',12,36,'en',22.00),(651,'z28y21u2q6ywttbl9uyzyd6j','南昌站','南昌站\n\n','九廣鐵路','1999 年 10 月 01 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>南昌站是西鐵第一期的南面總站，爲西鐵及地鐵東涌線之共用綜合車站。車站的結構，不但覆蓋了現有之西九龍高架高速公路及機場快線、地鐵東涌線，同時，也包括了相關的連接行車道路與高架橋樑系統。在車站建設施工期間，西九龍高架高速公路，機場快線及東涌線要保持如常運作，這些要求，爲施工帶來了不少難度。因此，對施工的技術要求亦十分高和嚴格。</p><br/><p>本車站設有地面沿車軌月臺及與地鐵東涌線共用的地底車站大堂。該大堂建於正在營運中之機場鐵路及東涌線的地底。爲確保機場鐵路及東涌線如常運作，所以特別選擇以「從上而下」（top-down）的建築方式興建，其規模爲香港僅見。地底車站大堂及月臺設計配合地下空間的儘量開發及善用，減少地面空間的佔用，亦確保地面外觀宏偉吸引，同時提供商業活動之餘，亦方便乘客流向的疏導，以高效率設計迅速將人流導至相鄰的機鐵車站、公共汽車站、住宅及商業區。</p><br/><p>爲配合未來在車站上蓋將會發展多幢多層式的住宅物業及高層商業大廈，車站的梁、柱結構及其基礎的設計作出了相應的預備工夫，其基礎包括多種不同類型的椿基：如大口徑現澆鋼筋混凝土攪拌椿、地下連續牆及打入式工字形鋼椿等等。車站施工期間，於車站頂部預留大樓底層之鋼筋混凝土柱結構。將來上蓋物業發展時，站頂平臺會以平板多肢結構承托上蓋的多層剪力牆，對未來上蓋樓宇設計時可産生的任何變動，是一個保留彈性的處理方法。</p>','2025-06-04 06:12:58.006000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.492000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.809000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',41.00),(652,'pbw0ekgzloczt47laihptckd','Contract No. KL/2015/03 Kai Tak Development – Stage 3B Infrastructure at Former North Apron Area','Contract No. KL/2015/03 Kai Tak Development – Stage 3B Infrastructure at Former North Apron Area','Civil Engineering and Development Department','22 December 2016 - 31 January 2022','<p>This project involves the construction of a section of dual two-lane Road L2, an elevated walkway LW4 across Prince Edward Road East and a 180m long pedestrian subway SW4 which connects the Kai Tak Development Area and Choi Hung Estate using trenchless method.</p><br/><p>The project utilizes Hong Kong&#x27;s first Rectangular Tunnel Boring Machine (RTBM), which enhances work safety and enables more effective management and control of tunnel construction risks. Additionally, the use of prefabricated tunnel segments produced at an off-site precast yard improves the quality of work and provides a safer work environment for the workers.</p>','2025-06-03 02:40:29.146000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.757000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.027000',12,36,'en',4.00),(653,'o6bwb49kal63x53v3xhswzof','Wan Chai Development Phase II - Central Wan Chai Bypass over MTR Tsuen Wan Line (Contract No. HK/2010/06)','Wan Chai Development Phase II - Central Wan Chai Bypass over MTR Tsuen Wan Line','Civil Engineering and Development Department','20 January 2011 - 15 July 2013','<p>The main purpose of the Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.</p><p>One of the contracts of Wan Chai Development Phase II, the works include land formation and construction of the Central-Wan Chai Bypass over MTR Tsuen Wan Line tunnel. As the tunnel must straddle the existing MTR Tsuen Wan Line, major constraint was anticipated during the construction. Since the span-over structure is a heavy massive box, an off-site pre-fabrication method was adopted to avoid imposing loading on the MTR Tsuen Wan Line tunnel. The completed box structure was towed to site by sea for final installation. This construction method proved to be more cost effective and did not cause any impact on the MTR Tsuen Wan Line during the construction.</p>','2025-06-03 03:49:01.346000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.670000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.013000',12,36,'en',18.00),(654,'mer5dsfeh84stflc656z3mcf','Civil and Infrastructure Works','Civil and Infrastructure Works','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 July 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The contract comprises the construction and installation, including the defined design elements, of all Civil and Infrastructure Works, on the West Rail Depot and Kam Tin Station Site. The Works include all site formation, drainage, roads and hard standings, utilities, landscaping, main drainage channel and track bed formation works. The scope of the roadworks includes construction of a two-lane viaduct bridge approximately 660m long across the site fire and public access roads, parking and inter-change facilities.</p>','2025-06-03 12:10:40.023000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.807000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.039000',3,36,'en',42.00),(655,'ab26i7pa3qwb8hxshw6n6l8l','望後石垃圾堆填區 合約G標段 – 衛生堆填及有關工程','望後石垃圾堆填區 合約G標段 – 衛生堆填及有關工程\n\n','土木工程署','1996 年 05 月 01 日 - 1997 年 09 月 30 日','<p>這個工程是望後石垃圾堆填工程最後一期工程。</p><p>主要工程包括：</p>','2025-06-04 06:20:05.220000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.854000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.125000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',50.00),(656,'gq0lawile6nf2mkavcazrces','Contract No. HY/2016/05 Footbridge connecting Tsuen Wan Plaza, Skyline Plaza and adjacent landscaping area','Contract No. HY/2016/05 Footbridge connecting Tsuen Wan Plaza, Skyline Plaza and adjacent landscaping area','Highways Department','08 May 2017 - 03 December 2019','<p>The major scope of this project consists of construction of a covered footbridge of about 66m in length and about 3.5m in clear width connecting Tsuen Wan Plaza, Skyline Plaza and adjacent landscaping area; construction of a lift and covered staircase at Hoi Shing Road, reconstruction of the existing lay-by at Hoi Shing Road and ancillary works including associated road, drainage, public utilities, lighting, landscaping, electrical and mechanical works, etc.</p>','2025-06-03 02:38:48.608000','2025-07-07 07:27:43.922000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.133000',12,36,'en',2.00),(657,'xaykyxnu4qn7aeizsinty750','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A','Remaining Engineering Infrastructure Works for Pak Shek Kok Development, Package 2A','Civil and Engineering Development Department','29 June 2004 - 15 October 2008','<p>This is the engineering infrastructure project for Pak Shek Kok Development.  The major works of the project consisted of a significant quantity of site formation works; and the construction of roads &amp; bridges, cycle track, water front promenade, subway, and the associated landscaping works, etc.</p>','2025-06-03 12:01:58.757000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.037000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.234000',3,36,'en',33.00),(658,'o479udtrplskn4jaohsr2lsk','Contract No. HK/2012/08 – Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central – Wan Chai Bypass at Wan Chai West','Contract No. HK/2012/08 – Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central – Wan Chai Bypass at Wan Chai West','Civil Engineering and Development Department','31 January 2013 - 28 November 2018','<p>The key purpose of Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.</p><p>This is one of the contract in Wan Chai Development Phase II. It is a large scale Reclamation Project with more than 5 Ha. in size. The Project&#x27;s location is from the Central Reclamation Phase III (CRIII) eastern seawall to the west of Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre Extension. The scope of work includes dredging works, seawall works, watermains laying, demolition of existing Expo Drive West Bridge, box culvert extension and stormwater drainage works.</p>','2025-06-03 02:56:53.532000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.070000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.287000',12,36,'en',13.00),(659,'bmlzogj0ibxsj3qfh59jypob','Improvement Works at Lo Wu Station Platforms 1-3, Link Bridge and Concourse Extension','Improvement Works at Lo Wu Station Platforms 1-3, Link Bridge and Concourse Extension','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','18 November 2002 - 30 July 2004','<p>The project included the installation of 156 nos. of vertical and raking mini piles with 273mm diameter to support the Concourse Extension of the Lo Wu Station and the Link Bridge linking the Concourse Extension to the existing Platform 1. The length of the piles constructed ranging from 20m to 40m with 5m long socket into Grade III rock. The piling works also included the Pre-Drilling prior to the commencement of the piling works to determine the rock head level and the target founding level. It also included the Proof Drilling subsequent to the completion of the pile installations.</p><br/><p>As all the works have to be carried out immediately next to the live railway tracks and inside the busy Lo Wu Station in full operation, the Contractor has to undertake all the necessary safety measures and arrangement to ensure that the train service and the operation of the Lo Wu Station will not be affected by the construction works.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 12:05:13.326000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.099000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.318000',3,36,'en',37.00),(660,'bsdeljdmebk1ky5hobm5tndj','Provision of Lifts to Two Footbridges across Wong Chuk Hang Road near Yip Kan Street and across Leighton Road and Irving Street; a Bridge across Tuen Mun Road near Tsing To Path and a Subway across Pak Wo Road near Fung Ying Sin Koon','Provision of Lifts to Two Footbridges across Wong Chuk Hang Road near Yip Kan Street and across Leighton Road and Irving Street; a Bridge across Tuen Mun Road near Tsing To Path and a Subway across Pak Wo Road near Fung Ying Sin Koon','Highways Department','01 July 2011 - 30 June 2014','<p>The Government is committed to help the elderly and persons with disabilities to get around town in a hassle-free way.　Barrier-free facilities have been installed at walkways for years. But with an aging population, the process needs to be sped up to make barrier-free access even more user-friendly. The Government have come up with this lift installation programme to provide a &quot;universally accessible&quot; environment.</p><br/><p>This is one of the projects of &quot;Universal Accessibility&quot; Programme which includes the construction of a total of six passenger lifts at two footbridges, one bridge and one subway; demolition and re-construction of three staircases and structural modifications of the footbridges/bridge/subway, associated lighting, drainage, utilities diversion and electrical and mechanical works.</p>','2025-06-03 03:50:08.626000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.024000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.328000',12,36,'en',19.00),(661,'liq1eaeghs1enjgfuzr4mlvh','Tung Chung Development Phase 1 – Infrastructure','Tung Chung Development Phase 1 – Infrastructure','Territory Development Department','01 July 1994 - 31 January 1997','<p>The bridge was supported by two land abutments and six marine piers. Each abutment was supported by twelve 1.5m diameter land bored piles up to 56m long and each marine pier was supported by twelve 1.5m diameter marine piles.</p><br/><p>The 1.5m diameter permanent linings of the marine bored piles were spliced into 24m to 30m lengths and pitched in position by piling barge.</p>','2025-06-03 12:22:51.933000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.260000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.500000',3,36,'en',53.00),(662,'muuu9xb5h09wlfjp8k3hz86k','Road L18A in AREA 18, Tuen Mun (Contract No.TM/2006/02)','Road L18A in AREA 18, Tuen Mun ','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 April 2007 - 29 May 2009','<p>The major works in this project consisted of the construction of an approx. 400m long and 10.3m wide two-lane carriageway with a 3.5m wide footpath on both sides section of about 160m long elevated structure over Wong Chu Road was constructed with a total of about 135m of retaining wall structure at both ends of the elevated structure.</p>','2025-06-03 03:57:24.912000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.394000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.595000',12,36,'en',26.00),(663,'vwvjud7i3d9wgqmgiem8upy8','沙田新市鎮五號幹線第一期連接工程','沙田新市鎮五號幹線第一期連接工程\n\n','拓展署','1987 年 06 月 01 日 - 1991 年 10 月 31 日','<p>這項計劃是興建沙田接駁城門隧道的工程，即連接沙田與荃灣的五號幹線高速公路。位於大埔道近九廣鐵路沙田站的2公里長的高速公路，在鐵路線及大埔道上跨越一條跨越高架橋的13條高架橋，沿著通往隧道口的路線往中途延伸。</p><br/><p>在美林村一段的快速公路一邊安裝了一至二米高，總長一公里之透明隔音牆，以減低噪音對附近居民的影響。</p><br/><p>鑒於樑柱接頭各尺寸不同的複雜性，本工程之鷹架亦需要特別訂制，主要分支撐用鋼架及結構腳手架兩種。</p><br/><p>本工程共使用四百八十六支後拉式預力U型樑，由於每支樑跨距甚大且重達六十五噸，故全為現場灌制，再由本公司自行設計建造之吊車吊裝定位。</p>','2025-06-04 06:24:55.105000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.436000','2025-07-07 07:27:44.648000',15,36,'zh-Hant-HK',56.00);
